author: {'steamid': '76561199210835669', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 68, 'playtime_forever': 122, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 122, 'last_played': 1710018923}
review:
Ele é bem divertido, ainda mais com amigos!

Jogabilidade rápida e dinâmica, conseguiram misturar tiro em primeira pessoa com futebol, por incrível que pareça deu certo.

Pena que o jogo está abandonado pela desenvolvedora e pelos jogadores, quando olhei no Steam DB havia apenas 8 pessoas jogando (isso que eu estava junto de 6 pessoas, então apenas 2 eram aleatórios e não os encontramos), potencial tem de monte, pena que ficou apenas no lançamento, gostaria muito que esse jogo voltasse a ativa.

Simplesmente não encontra partida, somente um servidor 3v3 com 200 de ping para cima, chegava a atrapalhar na jogabilidade o ping alto, mas como era o que tinha, então enfrentamos, legal que o jogo coloca bot's onde não tem players, então o time nunca fica faltando, aliás, o bot goleiro é bom demais tá dóido kkkkkkk.

Tá doido, tem hora que vira um verdadeiro Street Fighter kkkkk, gente se batendo e derrubando os outros, massa demais.

author: {'steamid': '76561198011595325', 'num_games_owned': 2477, 'num_reviews': 929, 'playtime_forever': 423, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 320, 'last_played': 1706231154}
review:
Supraball até que poderia ter sido um jogo melhor, mas têm muitos defeitos técnicos e se baseia quase completamente no multijogador, que está morto, literalmente TODOS os servidores estão desativados.
No tutorial você aprende a se movimentar, lançar a bola, derrubar adversários e defender o gol (entre outras coisas), depois que termina essa curto tutorial você pode procurar por uma partida online (nunca vai encontrar) ou jogar solo, o problema de jogar solo é que fica enjoativo rápido, mas principalmente o fato que o jogo apresenta vários bugs, trava no meio da partida, botões aparecem sem texto e ao termino de uma partida cria outra ignorando as configurações da primeira. Realmente o único motivo que estou rodando esse jogo é pelas steamcards, não recomendo nem de graça.
---------------------------------------------
Supraball could have been a better game, but it has many technical defects and is almost completely based on multiplayer, which is dead, literally ALL servers are disabled.
In the tutorial you learn how to move, throw the ball, knock down opponents and defend the goal (among other things), after finishing this short tutorial you can look for an online match (you'll never find one) or play solo, the problem with playing solo is that it gets boring quickly, but mainly the fact that the game has several bugs, crashes in the middle of the game, buttons appear without text and at the end of a game it creates another one ignoring the settings of the first. Really the only reason I'm running this game is for the steamcards, I don't recommend it even for free.

author: {'steamid': '76561198416760533', 'num_games_owned': 487, 'num_reviews': 433, 'playtime_forever': 29, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 29, 'last_played': 1703532137}
review:
[h1] Supraball: Not for Football Fans [/h1]

[b]🏃‍♂️ First Person Sports Game[/b] The game lets you play football from a first person perspective. You can develop your own tactics and moves and play with friends or alone. 🎮

[b]👥 Team Play[/b] The game emphasises team play. Since every player is human, everyone needs to work together for your team to succeed. 🤝

[h3] Cons: [/h3] [b]👎 Storytelling and Mods[/b] The game's storytelling and modes are almost non-existent. The game's storytelling and modes are not interesting and diverse. 📖😴

[b]👎 Visual and Graphic Quality[/b] Graphics are the biggest deficiency of the game. It is disappointingly bad for those who expect advanced graphics. 🖼️👎

[h3] Other Bad Points: [/h3] [b]👎 Limited Sound Effects and Variety[/b] The game's sound effects are as bad as the graphics. The sounds are not realistic and varied, spoiling the game experience. Better sound quality and variety are a must. 🎶❌

[b]👎 Multiplayer Experience[/b] The multiplayer experience of the game is also terrible. Servers are constantly closed or full, it is impossible to connect. Multiplayer options are boring and insufficient. It is far from meeting the expectations of the players. 🕹️👥
[b]👎 Replayability Issues[/b] Replayability is the game's biggest problem. The content of the game becomes boring and monotonous in a short time. 🔁🎮

[b]👎 Price and Content Balance[/b] There is clearly no balance between the price and content of the game. The price of the game is too high for the content offered. 👥👤

[b]👎 Technical Issues and Need for Improvement[/b] There are numerous technical issues in the game, ruining the players' gaming experience. Development and optimisation are sorely needed. ⚠️🔧

Supraball is not for football fans. Apart from being a first-person sports game and a team game, it has no other advantages. It has many shortcomings such as storytelling, graphic quality, sound, multiplayer experience, replayability, price and content balance, technical issues and the need for improvements. I would not recommend this game to anyone interested in football or sports games.

author: {'steamid': '76561198201246082', 'num_games_owned': 3232, 'num_reviews': 1499, 'playtime_forever': 32, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 32, 'last_played': 1655191106}
review:
Oyunda oyuncu yok!

Supraball, takım tabanlı bir online spor oyunudur. Supra Games tarafından geliştirilmiş ve yayınlanmıştır. Oyun, futbol benzeri bir oynanışa sahiptir ve oyuncular iki takıma ayrılır. Her takım altı oyuncudan oluşur ve oyuncular, topu hedefe atarak puan kazanmaya çalışır.

Oyun, oldukça hızlı tempolu ve zorlu bir oynanışa sahiptir. Oyuncular, topu kontrol etmek için çeşitli hareketler yapabilirler, örneğin topu havada tutabilir veya duvarlara vurarak topun hızını artırabilirler. Bu, oyuncuların oynanışı daha da geliştirmelerine olanak tanır ve oyunu daha heyecanlı hale getirir.

Supraball, oyunculara çeşitli oyun modları sunar. Oyuncular, takımlarıyla birlikte eşleşmelerde mücadele edebilirler veya özel bir maç oluşturabilirler. Ayrıca, oyuncular eğitim modunda pratik yapabilir ve oyunda daha iyi hale gelebilirler.

Oyunun grafikleri oldukça basit olsa da, oynanışı oldukça eğlenceli ve zorlu. Ancak, oyunun topluluğu oldukça küçük ve oyunun aktif oyuncu sayısı oldukça sınırlı. Ayrıca, oyunun bazı teknik sorunları var ve zaman zaman oyunda yaşanan gecikmeler ve bağlantı sorunları oyuncuların keyfini kaçırabiliyor.

Genel olarak, Supraball, futbol severler için eğlenceli bir alternatif olabilir. Ancak, oyunun küçük bir topluluğa sahip olması ve teknik sorunlarının olması, oyunun uzun vadeli başarısını sınırlandırabilir.

author: {'steamid': '76561198027308274', 'num_games_owned': 132, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 1135, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1135, 'last_played': 1604361757}
review:
Non fraintendetemi, ho amato questo gioco quando lo giocai anni fa, ma non posso consigliare un gioco che ormai non ha più un server funzionante, e che quindi è ingiocabile attualmente.
Ho atteso con ansia perché si vociferava di un Supraball 2, con champ con diverse abilità... ricordo che c'era anche un sondaggio da parte dello sviluppatore per avere più feedback possibili su cosa realmente la community volesse, ma, ahimè, non ha portato ad alcun risultato.

PRO:
- Gameplay geniale! Seriamente, questo gioco sembra semplice a primo impatto ma complicatissimo da masterare con tantissimi trick. Un gioco di squadra spettacolare che purtroppo nessuno potrà mai provare.

CONTRO:
- Abbandonato. Sarebbe potuto essere uno di quei giochi immortali, con contenuti dalla community come Trackmania, Garry's Mod e via dicendo, ma sarà probabilmente per i pochi fondi, il gioco è stato abbandonato, così come l'idea di creare un sequel che probabilmente avrebbe fatto un successo clamoroso (guarda per esempio Rocket League, che anch'esso è un sequel).
- Server chiusi. Motivo principale del motivo per il quale non consiglio questo gioco, è che i server non funzionano più. Non potete neanche giocare in coop con i vostri amici contro i bot.

Se state leggendo questa recensione non provate il gioco. Non potete fare nulla, se non giocare partite contro bot che, come quelli di Rocket League, non danno nessuna soddisfazione, obiettivi o robe del genere.

author: {'steamid': '76561198963046802', 'num_games_owned': 141, 'num_reviews': 147, 'playtime_forever': 12, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 11, 'last_played': 1670081189}
review:
If you're looking for a review on this game you've come to the wrong place, but if your're looking for an outstanding pie recipe you've come to the right place.

Ingredients:
1. 6 tablespoons unsalted butter
2. 1/2 cup white sugar
3. 1/2 cup brown sugar
4. 1/4 cup water
5. 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
6. 1 pinch salt
7. 5 apples - peeled, cored and sliced
8. 1 pastry for double-crust pie

Directions:
1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).
2. Combine butter, white sugar, brown sugar, water, cinnamon, and salt in a saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and set aside.
3. Roll out half the pastry to fit a 9-inch pie plate. Place bottom crust in pie plate; pour in apple slices.
4. Roll out top crust into a 10-inch circle. Cut into 8 (1-inch) wide strips with a sharp paring knife or pastry wheel. Weave the pastry strips, one at a time, into a lattice pattern. Fold the ends of the lattice strips under the edge of the bottom crust and crimp to seal.
5. Pour butter-sugar mixture over top of pie, coating the lattice, and allowing any remaining sauce to drizzle through the crust.
6. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and bake until the crust is golden brown, the caramel on the top crust is set, and the apple filling is bubbling, 35 to 40 more minutes. Allow to cool completely before slicing.

review:
This game is nice but here is a Muffins recepie:
Ingredients
2 medium eggs
125ml vegetable oil
250ml semi-skimmed milk
250g golden caster sugar
400g self-raising flour (or same quantity plain flour and 3 tsp baking powder)
1 tsp salt
100g chocolate chips or dried fruit such as sultanas or dried cherries (optional)

STEP 1
Heat oven to 200C/180C fan/gas 6. Line 2 muffin trays with paper muffin cases. In a large bowl beat 2 medium eggs lightly with a handheld electric mixer for 1 min.

STEP 2
Add 125ml vegetable oil and 250ml semi-skimmed milk and beat until just combined then add 250g golden caster sugar and whisk until you have a smooth batter.

STEP 3
Sift in 400g self-raising flour and 1 tsp salt (or 400g plain flour and 3 tsp baking powder if using) then mix until just smooth. Be careful not to over-mix the batter as this will make the muffins tough.

STEP 4
Stir in 100g chocolate chips or dried fruit if using.

STEP 5
Fill muffin cases two-thirds full and bake for 20-25 mins, until risen, firm to the touch and a skewer inserted in the middle comes out clean. If the trays will not fit on 1 shelf, swap the shelves around after 15 mins of cooking.

STEP 6
Leave the muffins in the tin to cool for a few mins and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

author: {'steamid': '76561198039341497', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 191, 'playtime_forever': 18, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 18, 'last_played': 1649321507}
review:
[h1]I'VE PLAYED A 20-MINUTES LONG TUTORIAL SO YOU DONT HAVE TO.[/h1]

the game starts with a forced tutorial, in which you have to repeat actions many times, and in some instances 3 times in a row. 
This is extremely boring and mind-numbing. 
at the very end you have to be the keeper, and catch or deflect the ball 12 (TWELVE) times.
then you are stuck in an un-skippable cutscene.
[spoiler]having fun yet?[/spoiler]

and then, finally, you can be placed in an infinite queue to find players.
yes, infinite, because [url=https://steamdb.info/app/321400/] there are 10 players playing at the time of review. [/url]  
the game is dead, and quite honestly that's for the better.

review:
I really like this game ive played almost 200 hours of it. if youre looking for a fun single player game that is quick to get into and you can play for 5 mintues to hours at a time this is it. the single player has been really fun imo. there are many different difficulties to play at so it has been fun getting better at the game so you can play against harder cpu's. Plus its free
That being said, the multiplayer isn't good. It is nearly impossible to find other people to play against so don't play this if youre looking for some matchmaking multiplayer gameplay

review:
Это просто "ВАУ" ! Очень интересная, весёлая и прикольная игруха. Играю каждый день со своими друзьями и в одиночку. Никогда ещё не пропадал интерес к игре. Очень нравится. Хороший геймплэй , графика и атмосферность. Всем советую сыграть в эту игру, не пожалеете !!!

It's just "WOW"! Very interesting, fun and cool game. I play every day with my friends and alone. Never lost interest in the game. Really like. Good gameplay, graphics and atmosphere. I advise everyone to play this game, you will not regret it !!!

author: {'steamid': '76561198071518796', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 54, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 54, 'last_played': 1514006408}
review:
This game is sooo good hahaaha :P get it!!! lol

..... *looks side to side* Is the coast clear? Phew, ok. I promised a couple developers I wouldn't budge, but I just can't keep quiet. One adjective I could use to describe this game? moneymaker. So ya wanna get rich, huh? Like Rich rich? Like Wolf-Of-Wallstreet-Penthouse-in-Manhattan-vacation-home-in-Barcelona type of money? Well let me tell you about a little game called Supraball. I was first introduced to this game by one of my investing buddies at work. We were on the Subway train down on Greenwood one morning on the way to work (Goldman Sachs, Senior Investment manager) and he nudged my shoulder.

"You interested in makin' a little money, Isaac?"

"Uh... yeah..?"

"You gotta get this game called supraball."

The rest is history. I've been hooked ever since. I get off work, make dinner, and usually stay up all night playing this game. 

So how do you make money, you may be asking? Read your mind, huh? Heh, you could say I'm a little intelligent lol. (SAT - 1550 , ACT - 36)

Lets just say.... the Market for Supraball is often compared to the likes of late-stage-capitalism-CEO-heaven. Basically you get these things called lootkits. These lootkits take $10.00 to open, and you have the chance to lose money, break even, and make more money. The trick is you basically buy a lot of lootkits and either break even or make money. With that money you buy more lootkits. Soon, you'll be asking yourself... what's that sound? It's quarters hitting the bottom of your piggy bank. Those quarters soon turn to dollars, dollars turn to thousands of dollars, you get the point. 

Oh, and the buyers market? A sellers dream. Buyers are basically drooling at the chance to buy these items. If you haven't seen the news lately, Supraball has broken a couple records for most players in a single multiplayer online game. Guinness approved. Most legendary items in this game are some of the most sought after items in the history of internet gaming. Needless to say, you won't have any trouble getting these items off your hands. 

So now you got the scoop, it's up to you what to do with this information. All I can say is... 

you in?

author: {'steamid': '76561198028570547', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2563, 'playtime_forever': 603, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 603, 'last_played': 1629926477}
review:
[h1]KOSTENLOS[/h1]

"Supraball" ist eine First-Person Fun-Fußball Variante.

Wobei Fußball eigentlich eine falsche Beschreibung ist, denn gespielt wird der Ball nicht mit dem Fuß, sondern mit einer Kanone, deren Schuß man aufladen kann, die aber auch in der Lage ist einen Ball in der Nähe anzuziehen. Auch können wir dem Ball einen Links- oder Rechtsdrall geben oder zu einem Mitspieler passen. Zudem können wir selbst durch Mehrfachsprünge eine erstaunliche Höhe erreichen oder ein Kraftfeld um uns erzeugen.

Vieles erinnert aber wirklich an Fußball. Es gibt zwei Tore, wir spielen auf Rasen und auch die Markierungen sind wie beim Fußball. Allerdings ist die Anzahl der Spieler reduziert. Besetzen können wir jede Position, auch den Torwart.

Gedacht ist das Spiel eigentlich als Multiplayer-Titel, auch wenn man gegen Bots kämpfen kann, was allerdings schnell langweilig wird. Und als Multiplayer-Titel würde "Supraball" auch reichlich Spaß machen, denn vieles am Gameplay stimmt. Geschwindigkeit, Handling und Bewegung sind direkt und gut kontrollierbar.

Das Problem ist, daß es leider keine offiziellen Server mehr gibt. Und das ist wirklich schade, bei einem so guten Titel. 

Einen Daumen runter kann ich trotzdem nicht geben, denn erstens ist das Game einfach richtig gut und zweitens ist es kostenlos, so daß man durchaus mal reinschauen kann und zumindest gegen Bots einige Partien machen kann. 

[h1]Wertung:[/h1]
7/10 Atmosphäre
-/10 Story
7/10 Grafik
6/10 Sound
7/10 Spielmechanik
7/10 Balancing
7/10 Spielspass

[h1]Fazit:[/h1]
Spaßiges Gekicke, leider nur noch gegen Bots.

[h1][b]6/10 Gesamtwertung (Abwertung wegen fehlender Server)

author: {'steamid': '76561198068880445', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 24, 'playtime_forever': 1155, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1155, 'last_played': 1518024690}
review:
[h1] Supraball - 5.8/10 [/h1]


[b]  Supraball: first person shooter mayhem on a soccer field  [/b]

Action-oriented sports games and PCs, for some reason, never seem to get along very well. There are a few out there, sure, but the big names just refuse to stray away from the console space. No matter: we are PC gamers, and we'll invent our own sports games. Enter: Supraball , a first-person reimagining of soccer in the Unreal engine.

Back in 2003, an Unreal Tournament mod called Deathball made the rounds to much acclaim. But since then, there haven't been many other attempts to put players into a first-person sports game. eSports , as fun as it is, is more focused on the competitive nature of more traditional first-person shooters. Supraball is something entirely different, with its cartoony graphics and lack of gore.

The game is free to download, host, and play until it's ready to come out of beta for a full release. If a meaningful league system and community develops to support this game and others like it, it's easy to imagine that Supraball represents one possible future of eSports competition. Head to Supraball's site to download the current build.

review:
Ho conosciuto questo gioco quando era ancora in accesso anticipato nel 2014. Era divertentissimo, uno gameplay completamente nuovo che mi ha appassionato fino dall'inizio.
Ho deciso di riscaricare il gioco oggi. Purtroppo ho notato che non ci sono giocatori online. E' un peccato, vorrei che più persone ci giocassero, anche perchè è free to play.
Ottimo lavoro sviluppatori, sfortunatamente i giocatori non hanno gusto.

I got in touch with this game when it was still in early access in 2014. It was hilarious, completely new gameplay that I was hooked on from the start.
I decided to re-download the game today. Unfortunately I noticed that there are no online players. It's a shame, I would like more people to play it, also because it's free to play.
Great job developers, unfortunately the players have no taste.

author: {'steamid': '76561198154247618', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 84, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 84, 'last_played': 1602252601}
review:
I wish I could give this a neutral. I gave this game a thumbs down although I do believe the concept has potential. The gameplay is fun and very enjoyable, the AI work well at least for a noob like me and I didn't experience any glitches. On the downside, either the playerbase for online is non existent or the servers are poor. I couldn't get into one without it disconnecting. The furthest I got was to a black screen. Also they need to imbed the search and setup function for the game. It was so annoying tabbing out to change settings. The game would freeze most of the time after the match had finished and just overall a lack of customisation and gameplay features.

You can check out my thoughts, fails and fun moments here for this game here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fs834GbfpFw

review:
Das Game hat ein schönes Spielprinzip, mit einem guten Tutorial. Könnte sogar wirklich Spaß machen, wenn die Server funktionieren würden. Konnte leider mit/gegen einen Kumpel kein einziges Spiel spielen. Jedes mal stand da, dass wir die Verbindung verloren haben. Auch unabhängig von einander.
-

review: Portal is perfect. Portal 2 is not. It's something better than that. It's human: hot-blooded, silly, poignant, irreverent, base, ingenious and loving. author: {'steamid': '76561199023839929', 'num_games_owned': 40, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 457, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 334, 'last_played': 1593009067}
review:
(+)Very fun to play game. For now I don't know a lot of tactics or use some of the special types of shots and passes well but still I have a lot of fun playing it.
(-) The only issue I have with it is servers and a number of players. Sometimes the server crashes mid game and you have to close the whole game and open it once more because if you don't it will have a problem to connect you to another game.
(-) numer of players is a issue because sometimes it is hard to find a game. We tried to play 3vs3 with friends but it was almost impossible to find other players to play so we had to search for any available game. 

I am shocked why the number of players is so low in this game because it is such a fun game with possibility to be even more fun with few updates and changes.

Overall super fun. I don't know if developers abandoned it but i really hope they didn't because it has a great potential. Even to be next big esport.

review: В этой игре есть потенциал, но ёбаные вылеты после каждого второго матча не дают этой игре никакого шанса: это невероятное говно, которое полностью портит все впечатления об игре. Зайти в игру впятером и искать игру пять минут, в итоге начать против ботов, отсосать им и на следующий матч у вас всё зависнет - вот, что вас ждет, не играйте, сыкономьте ваши нервные клетки и время. Говно.

author: {'steamid': '76561198293103595', 'num_games_owned': 30, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 512, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 405, 'last_played': 1591315054}
review:
A game that has great ideas and intentions, but is probably not executed in the way it wants to be. The graphics and sound are really in depth and capture what the game should be, however the actual gameplay mechanics are a bit hazy. Supraball’s starting menu has all the features out in the open and there for you to explore, but fails to indicate which button does which action. As some of you may have seen already, the GUI on the menu is very compactly squashed together creating an ugly appearance to the start of the game, already. Your statistics can be seen in the bottom right corner along with character customisation on the left, however anything else on the screen is unnecessary and shouldn’t be there. Overall the menu could be improved but shows you everything  you need for playing the game. 
  
  When playing in Supraball’s servers, you may notice that they are a bit empty, so to comeback this problem the developers (Supra Games) added supposed basic bots which enable empty games to play on. These bots are not very sophisticated and are extremely predictable in certain games, creating a boring and endless match. Not only that, they can also be very overpowered and show strong signs of teamwork - that is uncommon in players that may be new to the game or ones that have never met each other - as they are programmed to know each and every move. On the other hand, the bots can be a very useful teammate in difficult situations and will provide you with the best tactics possible for that match! 

  Now, the actual game play itself is amazing and smooth! Each game is structured to play multiple rounds within a certain time limit, yet when a team scores, a new round starts. If a round takes too long to finish and one team is having the ball too much, then the ball will be given to the opposite team to play, which I personally find a great touch to the mechanics. A tutorial can be found in the main menu, teaching you all the features and moves you will need to use in a game of Supraball. So if you need help, you know where to go! Players can play in different positions, such as: Goalie, Defender and Attacker and these positions will dictate how many points you get for each action you do. At the end of the match, the top 3 players will be displayed on a podium, which depends on how many points you earned in that match too. All games are surrounded by a stadium or a themed area which looks wonderfully stunning, creating a similar atmosphere to a football / rugby game.

  Overall I soley recommend Supraball, although it has it’s bugs and issues, but it was released nearly a year and those bugs are sure to be ironed out. The game play mechanics and the small detailed features show off the game even though I don’t think it is finished at all. You will be sure to have a great time playing, especially with friends that get competitive. And who’s to complain at a free game?

8/10

review: Very fun, very fast, very...varied? A handful of control options make for a massive difference in how to get down the pitch and stuff the net. When I was practicing before joining my friends online, the tutorial was straightforward and got me on the pitch pretty quick, and the game was a lot of fun with my friends trying to control the ball. It gets a little frustrating at bits when you're playing with people with more experience than you, but luckily this game gives you the option to play the AI, so you don't have to jump straight in against human players. It definitely fills the role of a party game with friends.

author: {'steamid': '76561198118560077', 'num_games_owned': 229, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 742, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 682, 'last_played': 1641694101}
review: From my time playing this game, I have found that it is one of the best physics based games I've played. The engine is fun and for the most part pretty consistent mechanics. Every once and while you get a thing where you probably should have grabbed it or maybe the enemy goalie was right there and probably should have saved your shot. But that's understandable and not a big issue. The actual game is very intuitive and fun to get better at. With the ability to work on things and master them with your friends to get some teamwork and plays going.  I do understand and respect the design choice for ranked to not allow parties. It is still fun to queue into ranked and get thrown with some teammates and to have to adapt. If you look at it and say, "THIS IS DIFFERENT I DON'T LIKE THAT" you wont enjoy ranked. I've only played a few ranked games but it was super fun to try and adapt to your teammates and the enemy. The engine that the engine in which the game opens up in is a bit clunky. But that doesn't undermine the fact of how amazing the actual game is. It can just be a little weird sometimes. You will face a lot of bots but it comes from a low playerbase but there's not a lot the devs can do about things like that. My review is mostly based on enjoyment of the actual game. On the basic mechanics and concepts that the devs programmed. the controls are fun and understandable. The game has a grounding based on simple but amazing mechanics. Supraball probably will never have a large Esport league or huge playerbase like other games its compared to I.E Rocket League. But just comparing it to games like that serves this game a huge dis-service. The game is one of my go to games to just relax and mess around with some bots or some friends and to just have fun with. For what it is, a free to play physics based game. It was made over the years by just overall love for the concept and the game sculpted it into a fun game that is very enjoyable. So mad respect to David. Keep up the good work Supra Games. :)

author: {'steamid': '76561198003818180', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1599, 'playtime_forever': 417, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 417, 'last_played': 1567773584}
review:
When you’re not playing Supraball at 300+ ping, it can be seriously fun with friends that know how to play. There is no such thing as “off side” in Supraball, it’s no rules, all play. The bonus of being able to shoot people out of the air if you’re close to them adds that brutal side to Supraball, and it’s what also makes it so unique from the other soccer / party games. I really think Supraball could be a common party game with friends, if only it had more people playing it, the polish is there, the gameplay is amazing, but the playerbase is almost nonexistent.

PROS:

-Unique way to play soccer
-Excellent sound design and graphics
-Fun with friends

CONS:

-Poor netcode for higher than normal ping
-No variations to map design besides looks
-Weak player base

author: {'steamid': '76561198417236945', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 32, 'playtime_forever': 39387, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 22863, 'last_played': 1641764107}
review:
Been playing the game since almost 5 months now. At first it's difficult to get used to all the controls, but that problem disappears after a few days/weeks. Supraball helps with your aim, quick thinking and team game (well, only if you're willing to play in a team).

The community is as much of a pro as a con: you can find friendly ppl and toxic ones too. The higher-lvl players know each other (at least by usernames), so it has that 'big, dysfunctional family' feeling to it once you advance to a certain lvl.
[Edit: Umm, maybe change that "big" to "medium and decreasing". New players leave the game after a few days, it's rare to see a higher lvl player who I've never met, sadly.]

Even if it's free, even if it has several good qualities, I can't recommend Supraball because the servers crash down every 1-2 weeks. Not just for hours - for 2-3 days or more, (seemingly) without any reason. And so far nothing has been done to solve this situation, which is pretty sad, considering that we're talking about a problem that has been here for months (or even longer).
[Edit: The crashes have been gone for a long time now! There are only lags remaining, lol.]

I could go on and on detailing Supraball's strong points and weaknesses, but I'mma just end this here: even though I don't recommend this game for a long-lasting time [edit: only if you're okay with playing against/with the same like 30-40 ppl + some newbies], it's still fun and enjoyable when it works properly.

review:
Tato hra by byla velice dobrá a zábavná, kdyby na ni vývojáři nesrali.

Zde jsou dvě důležité věci co tu hru *****.

                                                                                     1. Než se připojíte do zápasu uběhne 30 min.
       

                                2. Když už se po 30 min. dostanete do zápasu, na konci zápasu, těsně před vaší výhrou se vám to sekne, uvidíte všechny běhat na místě, po chvílí vás to zamrazí i ve výskoku a můžete se jedině odpojit ze hry a a čekat dalších 30 min. na nový zápas kde se vám to zase sekne. 
Dobré že. A ještě bych chtěl napsat že jsou tam jen nooby co hrají jen s shildem odráží míč od stěn a následně to kopnou do brány, 2 km dlouhé brány z půl metru.

author: {'steamid': '76561197992153921', 'num_games_owned': 162, 'num_reviews': 44, 'playtime_forever': 77, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 77, 'last_played': 1555097875}
review:
i understand the fad /trend 

people want Esports

but this is just dumb.

it's like Quake Rocket Arena mixed with TINY tennis balls....     in the style of FOOTBALL    (soccer)

it might sound appealing,   but it's not a good combo.
you might want to dismiss me by saying "git gud"

but when the player cant move fast enough to intercept each other... it gets annoying as they quad jump through the air passing to each other.
it's tested and confirmed,  you just cant move to intercept
the only way to kind of play is to "cover" an opponent... but the quad jumps and "attack three times just to drop the ball"  is fucking stupid.
why require three attacks?
why not just have a steal technique?
or some kind of jedi "force push" and pushes the ball out of their hand?

im trying to express the rise and fall (empty niches of unbalance)

and alot of pretentious elements that dont really contribute to a GOOD experience.

the same guy who carried the ball down the field can just QUAD jump OVER THE HEAD OF THE KEEPER
and because you can literaly just.... aim.... you just shoot whatever corner of the net the keeper isnt in.
oh quad jumps doesnt mean the keeper can move faster,  it just means you can jump jump jump jump into the goal zone and shoot down...
so it's really annoying being the keeper,  as they dont even need to reposition to shoot whatever corner of the net... just simply be above the net and shoot down into it.
and ill state one last time that the keeper just doesnt move fast enough even if the player has the response time.
and you gotta consider the guy can SHOOT from within the keeper boundaries....
so you CARRY the ball  (as in no skill involved "dribbling" technique required) inside the boundaries,  then quad jump too high to catch,   mouse sensitivity at 10.99999 so you can instantly AIM at whatever corner.... score.

i mean sure,  you scored... but the entire game is just catching the ball and quad jumping above the net.

this is just what teh community needs to do with the game "as is"
i dont know if the dev intended for people to CARRY the ball as they quad jump above the net and use their first person shooter skills to aim at any given corner of the net the keeper happens to not be able to reach.

maybe if they just rearranged things.... like NOT trying to immitate football... maybe should have tried hockey with a smaller net..
i mean... the players pick up the tiny "tennis ball size" and literaly point with the mouse and throw it.
so... why make it like soccer with a huge net but then gimp the keeper???
why not make it so the player automatically drops the ball when they jump???
or make it drop after the 2nd jump.....    like one jump is fine but if you double jump you drop the ball.... THAT WAY QUAD JUMPS HAVE A FUCKING PURPOSE
or .... why the fuck not have a basketball hoop instead???
i mean hockey net,  basketball hoop.. hello?!?!

smh
there's other free to play games that balance a whole lot better.

author: {'steamid': '76561198354327280', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 224, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 212, 'last_played': 1565363959}
review:
Dieses Spiel ist der absolute Dreck. Es ist verbuggt, die Tastenbelegungen ändern sich während des Spiels auf scheiß XBox controls, ich habe nicht mal einen verdammten xbox-Controller und ich war nicht der einzige, der das Problem hatte. Die Menüs sind unübersichtlich, voller bugs und hässlich. Das Gameplay selbst ist extrem frustrierend, wenig skillbasiert abgesehen davon, dass man gegen jemanden mit viel Übung nichts tun kann, da er die Spielmechaniken so ausnutzt, dass es keine Gegenstrategien gibt. Wenn man Spaß mit einem Fußballspiel haben will, sollte man sich definitiv Rocket League kaufen. Teilweise habe ich mit meinen Freunden 15:0 verloren, was einfach nur lächerlich ist, da wir uns wirklich Mühe gegeben haben und auch nicht wenige Spiele gewonnen hatten. In manchen Nahkampfsituationen wird der Bildschirm komplett rot, gleichzeitig wechselt bis zu 5 Mal pro Sekunde der Ballbesitz, was dafür sorgt, dass ein Angriff auf einen Gegner mit Ballbesitz daraus besteht, dass man den Ball kriegt, sofort wieder wegschießt, noch in der gleichen Sekunde wiederbekommt und niedergeschlagen wird.
Man kann das Spiel nicht ernstnehmen.

[list]
[*]Grafik 2/10
[*]Gameplay 3/10
[*]Wiederspielwert 1/10
[*]Gamedesign Scheiße, wie kann man ein Fußballspiel so verkacken 0/10
[/list]

Insgesamt: [b] Nicht den Download wert, macht keinen Spaß, frustrierend und verbuggt. [u]Tut es euch nicht an! [/u][/b]

Edit: Immernoch Müll!

author: {'steamid': '76561198333420603', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 453, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 185, 'last_played': 1554871667}
review:
This game is shockingly fun and has the flavor of rocketleague, with a cool first-person shooter like feel.  That said, it leans far further into the competitive game category than the FPS category, and is easy to get lost in for hours at a time.

The pay walls are all based around items that seem to have no effect on the game other then cosmetic - nothing you HAVE to buy - but i can see why people do at .75 cents a pop.  And although the current build is rough around the edges, with party-related bugs (mostly around the ability to join a new game after completing the first, without reforming the party) and the occasional random unbinding of keys for no reason (2 minute fix) - it's undeniably fun and entertaining...particularly at a $0 price point.

When it's Free to begin with - i can't see a reason not to at least try it.  Having tons of fun.

author: {'steamid': '76561198147032802', 'num_games_owned': 102, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 235, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 101, 'last_played': 1553959079}
review:
「Rocket League」とFPSが合体したようなゲーム。
操作感は、FPSであるため、「Rocket League」と比較すると初めてでも直感的に操作しやすく、チュートリアルでこのゲームにおいて重要な操作を理解することができるので良いと思った。

ゲーム性においては、ボールをシュートするにしても複数の手段があり連携なども可能なことから、練習すれば非常にテクニカルなプレイをする事ができ、とても楽しい。その辺は正に「Rocket League」と同じである。

このゲームの欠点を上げるとすれば、過疎っていて大抵の試合はCPUとプレイヤーの混戦となってしまうことと、立体的な自由度の高い動きに加え試合展開もハイスピードなので個人差はあるが比較的3D酔いしやすいといった部分だろうか。
しかしこのゲームは無料なので、ぜひ一度は遊んでみてほしい。

review:
Supraball is a game beyond the virtual impulses comprising the identity of soccer. 
Supraball has opened a dimension beyond substance and straightforward facts.
A dimension revealing the inconvenient truth of the world.

So far, playing this game has reveal three truths:

-R-ape is necessary for social stability

-R-ape is a de facto disciplinary response

-Without r-ape, the achievement of man is nullified. 

Supraball also offers an interesting take on r-ape culture. If progression is for the normalization of sex,
then how bad is r-ape afterall? How bad is forcing a handshake? R-ape, for the best, will turn to an unpreferred 
social gesture.

author: {'steamid': '76561198024276119', 'num_games_owned': 471, 'num_reviews': 108, 'playtime_forever': 25, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 25, 'last_played': 1552110648}
review: Supraball is an okay game; It's more of a lite version of Lucioball from Overwatch but not as exciting. Personally if you want to play a game based soccer with an extra layer of skill/mechanics that affects gameplay, just get a game like Rocket League. The gameplay is somewhat okay however to even play in an online match you will need to progress through and complete the tutorial. Besides gameplay, the menu seems cluttered with options that you change in match being reset upon returning to the main menu; Only way to get around this is to change the settings on the main menu before starting a match. Furthermore, the game is overall pretty much dead since only a few hundred players are ever online playing the game at any given moment.

author: {'steamid': '76561198041108401', 'num_games_owned': 1219, 'num_reviews': 496, 'playtime_forever': 71, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 71, 'last_played': 1551813515}
review:
Best tutorial ever in all video games I ever played! Short, informative, interactive and funny. These are the first developers who actually prepare the new players for the possible shitstorm of the community and teach you how to votekick harrassers. Also the mention of the chat and team chat button is something I always missed in other multiplayer games. Very nice!

Unfortunately it's not my game. I also didn't like the equivalent Unreal Tournament mod "Deathball" which took the mode Bombing Run into a soccer court. But if you look for a 1st person Rocket League with a gun instead of a car this is for you.

author: {'steamid': '76561198274572025', 'num_games_owned': 254, 'num_reviews': 54, 'playtime_forever': 571, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 550, 'last_played': 1560380619}
review:
Really cool game, and well made.
The reason I rated this bad is that it's almost impossible to find a good game without getting external programs, which shouldn't have to be a thing. Auto-player balance is non-existent so you get 5 players on one team and 1 player on the other with a bunch of horrible bots. Got some toxic people in the community, never nice.

So many bugs makes the game the worst to play. The fact you can't sprint + charge throw as goalie is BS. The bots scoring on themselves as keeper is also BS. There are many more but those are the most prominent.

Absolutely trash text chat as well as a kicking mechanism that allows AFKs/People that are helping the other team to stay in the server if the opposing team wants them to.

author: {'steamid': '76561198066232775', 'num_games_owned': 108, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 1672, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 998, 'last_played': 1583458959}
review:
I never actually post reviews, but I enjoy this game so much that I was compelled to write this. This game may not be perfect (yet), but the game play and mechanics are phenomenal. 

I played this game years ago and love it then, but it was rough and the fan base wasn't big at all. So my young, easily distracted brain move onto the next game my friends were playing. But, this game is captivating enough to suck me back in years later. I have really high hopes for this game. I truly do. I believe this could be the future of esports. Supraball running on unreal engine 4 with VR support will be a game changer (which the creator put out a statement which says he's hoping? to port the game to UE4, I have dreams for VR). I will upgrade my rig just to experience it if/when it comes. 

Best of luck with the game. I really hope you achieve your dreams for my sake.

author: {'steamid': '76561198011846784', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 158, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 158, 'last_played': 1549931465}
review:
Had a lot of fun for the first 2 hours, then i started getting matched with level 20+ people. I don't care about losing, but i had a glimpse of what the game is played at higher levels, and it's just a big, sad mess. The "pass" button goes completely forgotten, everyone just shoot the ball very hard on a wall and tries to deflect it multiple times after every bounce. I ended up getting the hang of it, but IMHO the fun of the game just goes out of the window.

TL,DR: started playing a fun, footbally game - ended playing a couple of tennis-squash messy matches that made me uninstall without a second thought.
developer_response:
What you saw was not high level play. High level play requires very complex and intensive passing.

I'm sorry you got put in a match with too high level players. The more players are online, the better the matchmaking works.

it said, Start running in a straight line. 
> run in a straight line, doesn't do anything.

review:
Gioco fantastico dalle meccaniche davvero semplice.
Non parliamo di Rocket League dove la meccanica è l'abilità più importante!
Per quel po' che ho giocato non posso fare una recensione accurata ma posso dire che non c'è un Pay To Win anche perché non esiste un "Lanciatore di palla" più accurato o più forte quindi, dovete essere voi bravi nel smarcarvi e passare la palla al proprio compagno di squadra.
Ci ho giocato per pochissime ore solo perché non ci sono abbastanza giocatori quindi ho dovuto arrangiarmi con i BOT che messi alla massima difficoltà sono IMBATTIBILI!

review:
Buen Juego,Es Simple,Entretendio y Con Buenos Graficos
Lo Malo es que tiene un par de bugs como por ej....
al entrar de nuevo al juego se te pone el volumen fuerte (aunque la ultima vez lo pusiste bajo) o en vez de que aparesca tu nombre de steam en el juego,te aparece un nombre predeterminado del juego (EJ: Player777) y asi pasa aveces,cuando volves a la partida o cuando jugas (aunque si se lo cambias,se pone tu nombre de steam) pero,por otra parte el juego esta muy bueno para seguir estando en EA (Early Accesss) lo recomiendo para jugar solo o con amigos (si es que los tenes) y para pasar el rato marcando unos goles. y dejando atras los bugs lo recomiendo.

author: {'steamid': '76561197997676483', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 758, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 708, 'last_played': 1540243356}
review:
I can’t believe this game isn’t bursting at the seams with players. I downloaded it after reading a post on Reddit about how good it was for a free game and it’s safe to say I was hooked from the first match I played! This game needs more coverage!!

The graphics are simple and I usually care about them a lot but I can’t help but think if they were any more complex than they are it would take away from the core fun to play element of this game!

Brilliant job, 

From a very happy customer!

author: {'steamid': '76561197965861474', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 2689, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2586, 'last_played': 1546803876}
review:
HEy, I REALLY like the idea of this game.  But playing it is nearly impossible.   
Catching the ball when running is close to impossible.  (I am a god gamer with a nice setup and a good moouse. And I "was" REALLY good in Unreal Tournament long time ago. I KNOW how to handle my mouse)   But in Supraball: NO WAY

And the worst thing. Players cheat SOOO much.   Nearly all other players run twice as fast as "normal non cheating" players.  And yes I know about all the jump tricks while running in supraball etc.

Nide idea => really nice developers, who actually read their forum.  => But not so nice cheaters.
developer_response:
When there is a speedhacker, please just report that one to us and we'll ban.

You will figure out moving, catching, shooting etc all at once soon enough. It's movement patterns that don't happen in other games, so it's a new thing to learn for everyone at first.

author: {'steamid': '76561198041512403', 'num_games_owned': 1837, 'num_reviews': 2465, 'playtime_forever': 121, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 121, 'last_played': 1540713913}
review:
골대를 향해 슈팅!

공을 총에 넣어서 골대나 팀원에게 쏘는 게임입니다.
건에 넣은 상태에서 이동이 가능하며, 최대 4단 점프까지 가능하죠.
지정된 팀원을 향해서 직접적으로 패스를 하거나(우클릭)
특정 공간을 향해서 차징 방식으로 골을 쏠 수 있습니다.(좌클릭)
자신에게 오는 공을 특정 방향을 향해서 발리로 날릴 수도 있죠(휠 클릭 유지)

공을 소지하지 않은 상태에서 좌클릭을 하면 밀쳐내기가 가능합니다.
이를 통해서 공을 받지 않고 다른 곳으로 밀쳐낸다거나,
다른 선수들을 짧은 거리 밀쳐낼 수 있죠.
공을 가지고 있는 선수에게 하면 데미지도 줄 수 있죠!

다른 플레이어들을 보기가 힘들지만, 인공지능전도 꽤나 재밌습니다.
무엇보다 공을 흘릴 일이 크게 없어서 좋더군요.
물론, 위치 선정을 잘못하여 공을 의도치 않게 흘려버리는 경우도 있지만....

아쉬운 점
-사람이 안 보여요!
-튜토리얼이 은근 햇갈림

author: {'steamid': '76561198121412008', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 684, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 615, 'last_played': 1548535770}
review: Vous en avez marre d'attendre le sempiternel fifa, qui chaque année n'apporte que peu de modification à son gameplay ? Vous cherchez plus de fantasie, plus de dynamisme, alors ce jeu est fait pour vous, superball est un jeu à la première personne dans lequel vous incarnez un joueur d'un sport qui ressemble au foot, à ceci près que l'on joue ici avec une sorte d'arme à feu futuriste, qui vous permet d'aspirer/renvoyer/controler/tirer la balle avec différents degrés d'intensité, et ou d'utiliser des effets pour tromper vos adversaires. Les parties se déroulent en 3v3 ou en 5v5, jouer avec ses amis est fortement conseillé pour apréhender toute la dimension tactique du jeu et pour se payer une bonne tartine de fun. Bref, un jeu neuf, concentré d'énergie et de nervosité, rien de mieux pour occuper ses jours vide, tempérer son ennuie.

author: {'steamid': '76561198126213050', 'num_games_owned': 2930, 'num_reviews': 365, 'playtime_forever': 106, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 106, 'last_played': 1538840839}
review:
最大5vs5の一人称ハイスピード・アクションサッカー。

現状全く人はいないので、基本は自分以外全員CPUか味方が一人だけプレイヤーなレベルです。ただ結構CPUの頭が良いみたいで、どれかCPUか気付くのに時間が掛かりました。それぐらい自然でした。
プレイヤーか見分ける時はpingが変動したり、ポジションに表記があるのがプレイヤーです。出来ればフレンド9人集めて遊べれば一番面白いですが、6人集まれば3vs3もできるので、フレンドとやる時はなるべく多い方が良いです。ちゃんとPTも組めるので足りなくても大丈夫ですが。

ゲーム性は、とにかく試合スピードが速いです。Shiftでブーストジャンプ、普通のジャンプは3段階もあり、足で蹴るのではなく、手に持ったバトンにボールを捕まえたり弾くのでどんどん攻守が入れ替わったりします。
ボールを捕まえるとプレイヤーと一体になるので、ボールを持ったプレイヤーを二回蹴り飛ばすと気絶してボールが地面に落ちます。

それにシュートがかなり凝っていて、円ゲージを溜めれば溜める程シュートスピードが速くなり、QかEの押し具合によって左右のドライブが掛かってキーパーに捕まらないシュートが打てます。
ただ円ゲージがオーバーヒートしてしまうと失敗してボールが転がり落ちますが、この他にすぐさまボールを吐き出すクイックシュートに、飛んできたボールをそのまま弾き返すことも出来るのでセンタリングからゴールへ弾き入れたりも可能です。

個人的に『Rocket League』よりも直感的に自由に動きながら、トンデモシュートを決められるのが気持ち良いので過疎りつつも好きです。

author: {'steamid': '76561198833241134', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 74, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 74, 'last_played': 1538614730}
review:
Give it a shot! The tutorial is rather boring but very beneficial as it goes. Just get through it, then play a match with a friend or two. It has a lot of potential. For free? It's more than worth trying for. I feel this game would benefit greatly from controller bindings.

My one complaint... I think a third person view may be better. I hope, much like Rocket League, the mechanics and gameplay get smoothed out as it develops. It's already great as is but wwould be amazing smoothed out.

author: {'steamid': '76561198316913414', 'num_games_owned': 279, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 490, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 450, 'last_played': 1569669672}
review:
I have to say that I wasn't impressed when I saw Supraball for the first time. It seemed to me like a low-quality game like some of the $0.99 titles. The thing that persuaded me to try it is the fact that I got it for free. 

And I actually liked it. It is very exciting and competitive, it can run pretty well on low-end computers like mine and it's even F2P now with no P2W tactics. I believe that the game has a bright future awaiting for it and that the devs deserve support from everyone. One of the best games I've ever played.

author: {'steamid': '76561198069519613', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 128, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 128, 'last_played': 1535284295}
review:
This is a really great game, the graphics look great, it runs fairly well and it's a lot of fun, especially with friends. There are however some issues that really need worked on before I at least, play this game regularly. Here is a list of pros and cons.

Pros:
Great Graphics
Cool customization
Nice EXP system
Unique gameplay and mechanics
Fun gameplay and mechanics
Good for friends.
AI are not too weak or too hard and are good team players.

Cons
Sometimes, the goalie just catches it. They shouldn't be able too, but they do. (AI)

Sometimes, the goalie just doesn't catches it. It's nice because free points but it's an obvious and annoying glitch. (AI)

The servers for Oceania don't launch sometimes.

The kick button stopped working after my first time playing and wouldn't work since, preventing me from using it to score and making it impossible to KO other players that could KO me. My friend had the same issue after the first time they played.

Even with a Ping less than 30 lag teleports occur

Sometimes you kick in a direction you weren't pointing for no reason.

author: {'steamid': '76561198194043009', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 319, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 294, 'last_played': 1535504682}
review:
This game has a fun and simple concept along with cool features, nontheless the game needs some work and you can't blame it because it's Early Access. My review will contain useful constructive criticsm so I hope a developer reads this, thanks. :)

I'll go over the Pros first.
Progression System and Cosmetics: You get rewarded with cosmetic items for simply leveling up! Isn't that great? You don't have to spend money to get cool cosmetics, and even if you do, it's not that expensive. The cosmetics are pretty neat themselves too. Also this game isn't pay to win! [B+]

Controls and Difficulty: The default controls are simple enough and it depends on the player if they wanna change their controls. The tutorial goes over everything and isn't overly complicated, very good for new players. There is practically no learning curve, after an hour or two of playing you've pretty much learned it all. [A]


NOW LET'S GO OVER THE CONS 

THE MATCHMAKING: Atrocious, the game implements bots which is good when filling spots but more often than not the teams are unbalanced and sometimes you join a game where your bot only team is losing by 5 to the other team which has 4 players and only one bot. Another thing, maybe it's because not many people play, but you play with the same people over and over again, even if you leave and press Play, you end up joining the game you just left, there should be an option to allow you to look for a different game. This would also be very helpful in situations where you're losing by a lot by yourself on a bot only team and wanna just play a game where your enjoyment isn't ruined. [D-]

I also have a great idea that would help this matchmaking problem, implement a bot difficulty system. How would this work? Simple, if you only have one bot on your team out of 5, that bot should have an easy difficulty configuration, if you're by yourself, your bot teammates should have a much harder difficulty to be on par to other real players. Of course it's more compliacted than this but integrating it would make the game much more fair and enjoyable.

Gameplay: While overall the gameplay is very solid, there is one problem I have. I've started to notice a trend where a player will sit in front of the enemy team's goal to wait for a pass and easily score, and for some reason the bots ignore the player and it's a very cheap and unfair exploit, and I have two solutions. 1. Program the bots to mark the player in order to pressure them into moving, or 2. Integrate an offside rule like they use in soccer to avoid this scenario. Of course this would completely change the game but make it fair to everyone. But I understand if it's too complicated to add. [C+]

Overall the game is fun and it has is awesome moments, but these changes would make the game even better and attract more players while keeping the current ones. However in its current state, it's not an enjoyable experience, and hopefully the developers will fix these problems to make an amazing game. Thanks for reading.

Also one last thing, the optimization is pretty bad for such a simple game, I don't know why this game runs poorly compared to other games I play.

author: {'steamid': '76561197987468538', 'num_games_owned': 1409, 'num_reviews': 172, 'playtime_forever': 824, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 648, 'last_played': 1677696727}
review:
Instead of writing more about why we think this game is great we decided to let our beta testing community write some comments here.

"What is Supraball? - imagine you're playing fifa, controlling just one player. Okay now imagine that each other player is a real person. Okay now imagine you're in first person, and you have this super awesome cannon with dozens of combinations of spins that fires a yellow ball at 400km/h. Okay now imagine you've fired that into the top corner at that speed - and someone saves it. That is supraball!"
Solomon

"So the first thing that I liked was the innovation, there are no games like it."
Malaria

"The game being a first person sports game made me feel like I was actually on the field playing ball. Also, the fact that everyone on the playing field was an actual person, and not a scripted AI that would change into the player if given the ball, added an element I personally had never seen in a game before Supraball."
Skel

"F**k yes, I can play football at home!"
Silw

"The thing that fascinated me the most is the amount of teamwork involved and the kind of creativity you can have while playing this game."
Bakes

"It's pretty easy to play but hard to master."
Olo

"Most fascinating is the ability some players have to always create new moves etc."
Goku

"Different things happen every match, so it's never the same."
Dimle

"I liked being the last hope for my team and the tense pressure filled moments were amazing. Making a 1v1 save is a really awesome feeling and no other game has given me the same feeling yet."
Vendetta

"Very precise, accurate, total control. Intense gameplay, nail biting finishes.
I can't stop, it's heroin/crack!"

Absolutely love this: bags of potential for different styles and approaches to plays, but pretty simple controls that feel easy to pick up and tricky to master.

The lack of players is an issue that leads to friction because of uneven teams, however, for now. But this is only fixed if people play!

So. You know what to do if you're on the fence, eh? Just go play it. Try it. You'll probably love it.

author: {'steamid': '76561198345346629', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 1307, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 425, 'last_played': 1593019866}
review:
I downloaded this game three days ago. I am one of the noobs people keep complaining about. However, I am enjoying my experience. But if you are reading this and thinking, "great, I'll download this game"- please read on.

At it's core, this game is fantastic. It is far better than rocket league. It's fun, easy to learn and hard to master, and has terrific potential.

That being said, there are many things pretty much out of developer control that plague this game, and it's fully possible that these things will make you not enjoy the game. First, I have heard that while the game was in alpha it was great with a great community to back it up. Then, as I understand it, rocket league came out, development slowed, and it's great community of dedicated players slowly vanished. Unfortunately now it is just a shell of the game it used, and deserves to be.

The players that do remain are largely noobs like me, but if you are reading this review that probably doesn't bother you. What does bother me is that the community of noobs is still very small- there are barely any people playing this game, which to me is very sad. The self- appointed 'pro's' (not the ones in the video- the modern ones) are mostly people with 40 hours who are constantly pissed about all of the 'newbs' and immediately leave or insult you once you join one of their practice matches. 

Moreover, if you want to have a match against people that isn't with a bunch of bitchy 'pro's' or is not a practice match but a real one, good luck. You will have to either start you're own server, or play with one other person plus eight bots.

To be honest, I feel sorry for the dev who clearly has worked hard and made a great game (which I know from experience is hard), only to have it ruined by its community (or lack thereof).

I give a thumbs up because the game is fun, however I only intend to keep it until it comes out of early acces in order to see if when it does for some reason the player base expands, as I do not really enjoy playing with bots.

Honestly, for all of the complaining about 'noobs' you'll see, the best thing for this game is probably an influx of noobs like you, so if you intend to play and become an actual 'pro', please do download.

If not, then this is honestly not your cup of tea.

P.S.: To the dev, I hope this game regains poopularity it deserves and suceeds- it is SO much better than rocked league :)

author: {'steamid': '76561198096998302', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 1742, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1459, 'last_played': 1608744773}
review:
Played a LOT during the alpha and loved the game. The gameplay, the community (you played with the same people a lot but they were nice and servers were filled with people at all times) all of it. 

With the beta came numerous changes on the pitch as well as in the game as a whole. The game had a lot of potential e-sport wise but the development was relatively slow and with the arrival of Rocket League, the game barely held its playerbase even though, to me, this game is way better. If you want to play this game now, be aware of two things: you'll play with a lot of bots and the few real people that play will probably play for themselves (never passing or boosting or anything useful even though they just walk in a straight line) and they haven't come as friendly as they were during the alpha. Second thing and the most important, you'll never play this game at a 100%. You probably will never unveil its full potential, the players that have played the game for hundreds of hours have left and you'll never be able to see how the game can be played out in its full glory. This game is the shadow of its alpha which already seemed like the shadow of a, otherwise, great game. 
I thank the devs for putting a game like that out there and truly, I had a lot of fun. But if you want to pick the game up now, there is a good chance you'll play it once and then never open it again.
developer_response: So do you want there to be more or less players?

author: {'steamid': '76561198081295186', 'num_games_owned': 230, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 587, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 587, 'last_played': 1469218127}
review:
Grabbed this game when it cost money, now i feel scammed.

The main reason i brought it early was because i liked the concept that was shown. But what ruined my experience was that servers were either empty or full of people that had literally spent hundreds of hours in the game.

And the problem lies in how big the player base is. If the first thing you have to do is spend hours and hours practicing alone to have fun or even stand a chance against randoms, then something needs improvement in my eyes... Especially if its the kinda "easy to learn hard to master" game. No matter how fast you get better, you're almost always gonna be behind those you play with and against.

I recommend the game because i feel like it could be so much more than it is atm, if only the game had a bigger player base, which would make it easier for new players to get into the game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198059775796', 'num_games_owned': 369, 'num_reviews': 39, 'playtime_forever': 610, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 272, 'last_played': 1567778573}
review:
Ce jeu m'a tout simplement dégoûté. Au début, j'ai lancé le tutoriel je me suis dis "tiens ce jeu a du potentiel pour un F2P" mais au final, y'a seulement les bots qui ont une réelle conscience de l'esprit sportif. Le jeu est plutôt joli niveau graphismes et pas de potentiels bugs (je n'en ai jamais eu pour ma part). Mais par contre la communauté c'est full cancer à gogo. Déjà tu joues contre des levels 12 ou level 25, choses qui n'est pas censé lieu d'être, à la limite ces gens là devraient être un exemple pour nous. 
Au lieu de ça, ils se font un p'tit kiff personnel et aller que je me la joue perso, "j'te fais une passe mais t'es obligé de marquer" mais abruti quand on est level 2 et qu'on découvre la vitesse et l'adrénaline du jeu, on a pas le temps de faire des passes et de marquer parce que oui aussi, les adversaires sont h24 sur toi en train de te bastonner la gueule pour récupérer la balle aussi. Donc, tu n'as pas le temps de faire grand chose et encore moins de charger ton tir pour marquer.
Du coup c'est dommage parce que pour un jeu qui est censé être joué en team, on passe d'un jeu où c'est chacun pour sa gueule, chacun fait ses p'tits points de son côté.
A la limite je vous le recommande si vous jouez uniquement entre potes mais seulement entre potes.

(pour les rageux les commentaires sont ouverts, j'vous attends avec impatience)

author: {'steamid': '76561198074138313', 'num_games_owned': 1148, 'num_reviews': 906, 'playtime_forever': 1496, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 802, 'last_played': 1527932908}
review:
плюсы игры:
1. бесплатная
2. простая
3. веселая
4. не плохая графика
5. атмосферные звуки
6. кастомизация
7. продаваемые на торговой площадке вещи

минусы игры:
1. баги 
2. проблемы с авторизацией с серваками. иногда просто выкидывает во время игры, когда ты ведешь по мячам

в целом, отличный бесплатный футбол. всем рекомендую. разрабам спасибо за продаваемые вещи

author: {'steamid': '76561198074190161', 'num_games_owned': 2188, 'num_reviews': 684, 'playtime_forever': 3474, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2202, 'last_played': 1653903415}
review:
Очень увлекательный и необычный онлайн футбол.
Особенности игры:
*бесплатная игра
*отличный геймплей с хорошо прорисованной графикой
* замечательное музыкальное сопровождение
* игра 5 на 5 или 3 на 3
* возможность пройти обучение и понять смысл игры
* прикольная аркада внутри игры(по достижении нужного уровня)
* красивые видеозаставки
* костомизация персонажа под ваш вкус
* очень радует система дропа скинов в инвентарь стима

 Как не очень большой любитель спортивных игр я просто в  восторге от этой игры .
Однозначно всем советую её попробывать.
Как играть и получать скины смотрите в моём видео
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0pFQEp1_lx0

author: {'steamid': '76561198078071964', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 127, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 127, 'last_played': 1523319161}
review: I absolutely love this game. Its a simple yet very entertaining concept of football and even though I love to play this game whenever possible, I just unistalled. Why ? The severe lack of players on servers other than America. I could'nt find anyone on the South-East asia server and even the Oceania server to play with and constantly get matched up with full bots. Its sad that my venture in this game comes to an end but hopefully, Supraball grows and I may return. Till than, farewell.

review:
If you enjoy a first person shooter perspective, skilled and tactical gameplay then you should give Supraball a try. A fully non pay to win game ( as extra's are merely cosmetic). Thus it's the collective skill of the team that on average wins games and not some pay to win "weapon" etc as is the case in many other games.

The game is early access (beta stage of development) though is completely playable.

review:
Un ottimo passatempo, non può essere definito diversamente. 

Bisogna essere amanti del genere per apprezzare, simile al noto Rocket League di Psyonix Studios, ti catapulta (Ciao Maccio) in un'arena contro 3 o 5 giocatori dove bisogna disputare una partita di "calcio" piuttosto particolare.

Non male, da valutare anche il fatto che sia un Free to Play.

author: {'steamid': '76561198272416237', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 1691, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 883, 'last_played': 1656976253}
review:
A game with alot of potential. Here are some pros and cons:

Pros:

* Community is mostly friendly.
* Game mechanics are unique. Never seen a idea like this before.
* Cool In game items to keep you looking fresh.
* Free to play

Cons:

* You rarely play with a full server of people, 90% of all players you play, are bots.
* Laucher is a little bit messy, but understandable for a game in early access.

Conclusion: While playing this game now might be frustrating while in Early Acess with the low playerbase. In time I'm sure this game will grow a larger playerbase and continue to improve. What this game needs right now is more players, support and exposure and I'm sure it will grow to be the next big thing.

review:

Hopefully when they are out of early access, this will be more playable for me.

author: {'steamid': '76561198288427306', 'num_games_owned': 839, 'num_reviews': 60, 'playtime_forever': 178, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 178, 'last_played': 1520563054}
review:
Juego bastante entretenido, pero en el transcurso del mismo se vuelve pesado y hasta un tanto aburrido, necesita mas modos de juegos y obviamente MEJORAR los servidores.
No puede ser que ya casi se cumplan 2 años desde la creación del juego (Yo forme parte de la fase beta, gracias a dios que no me gaste $10 en esto), y todavia no hay servidors latinoamericanos, basicamente no existen servidores fuera del continente Europeo y de  Norteamérica.
Recomiendo jugarlo con 1 o mas amigos, eso si, cuando por fin se digne la gente a participar de este juego, ya que el problema principal, es la carencia de modos de juego, de personas, y de desarrollo.

5/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198033726642', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 13, 'playtime_forever': 19924, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 7067, 'last_played': 1580601784}
review:
I'm amazed. At this point I think I've developed an unhealthy addiction and the only way to live through the day is more Supraball.

It starts off super innocent with you passing a few balls across the pitch, but there is just something about trying to be able to pull off that one move you saw that level 30 dude do... and Supraball is really the gift that keeps on giving, I've never felt like anything is unattainable or that I've learned it all. When you eventually start flying across the map scoring crazy volley goals, it's the most statisfying thing ever!

I've never been big into sports games but this one just scratches some itch that no other ever has. Maybe it's the super fast pace that almost remind me of egoshooters like Quake or UT or Sauerbraten. Maybe it's because all my friends spend half an hour configuring teams in FIFA and here I can just jump into a game. Maybe it's because the controls are really simple but lead to an amazing variety of gameplay.
Whatever it is, I've never quite played anything like Supraball, and I'd recommend everyone to try it!

author: {'steamid': '76561197962815481', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 7059, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2552, 'last_played': 1529708214}
review:
Very fun game when you can find matches (with people)

+ core mechanics really solid and enjoyable
+ team play experience is GREAT when bots are few to none and people aren't trolling
+ fast paced, possession is constantly changing, both defence and offence are 
+ F2P but in NO way P2W
+/- easy to learn, difficult to play well
+ low minimum specs

- only a few hours (in my exp) each weekday with enough people online to make it enjoyable
- few middle-skilled players
- UI is rough but getting better, player models are corny (who cares if the game is fun..)

Really enjoying the game so far. Playerbase isn't big but but seems salvageable at the moment. It doesn't really matter that the player models are wack, but if the devs are making money only through crates/costumes it might be good to improve them sooner than later.. really you don't notice/care in game though. 

Id recommend giving the game a shot if you enjoy fast paced team games even a little. Check steamcharts.com for when to play (evenings in US seem fine at the moment).

review:
Really cool concept,  I love the possibilities for team plays and whatnot.
[h1] What would I change? [/h1]
 A few things I would change though, one being the GUI such as the ingame and settings. Especially the settings, It would be better to make it more user-friendly making everything easier to see and find, and also giving it a nice game related theme rather than the dull grey box. Another thing I would change is the way the main menu and match windows are split. Having the game open to the home menu, and match window open in there is way more efficient and gives the game a cleaner look. 
[h1] Overall [/h1]
Other than that I'm having a lot of fun so far! The actual game is really fun to play, and movement is overall smooth.

author: {'steamid': '76561198095018876', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 14929, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 6941, 'last_played': 1579447440}
review:
Excellent jeu coopératif qui requiert un certain temps d'apprentissage mais les possibilités sont énormes.

Le tutorial très bien fait, et INDISPENSABLE avant de se lancer dans son premier match, explique les mécanismes de base.
Vous pourrez par la suite continuer à vous entrainer avec des bots ou revenir au tutorial pour vous exercer sur des points bien précis.

Une fois ce petit temps d'apprentissage passé, vous voilà prêt à intégrer une équipe pour une partie endiablée.

Le jeu en équipe est primordial. Pas question de se frayer un chemin tout seul jusqu'au but adverse (à moins d'être un vrai pro et de jouer contre de pauvres newbies fraichement débarqués) sans faire de passes et veiller à se placer de manière intelligente.
Sur le terrain chacun à un rôle: 1 gardien, 1 défenseur, 3 milieux/avants. Le rôle qui vous est attribué change d'une partie à l'autre.

Lorsque tout le monde joue vraiment le jeu, les parties sont extrêmement prenantes.

Bonne communauté, et il n'est pas rare (du moins sur les server EU) d'avoir l'occasion de faire une partie avec un membre de l'équipe dev, qui apporte régulièrement des updates.

En bref un must à posséder absolument pour tous les amoureux de sport vidéoludique !

author: {'steamid': '76561198020913432', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 1807, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1774, 'last_played': 1706366022}
review:
At first enjoyed it a lot (first few hours). After a while realized I was playing mostly against BOTs - no passing, kicking the ball all the time (usually powered/spinned towards the goal), no team work - just let the ball bounce all over the place.
Even if you end up playing with couple of humans, the AI makes it so bad. Don't get me wrong - first impression was really amazing, something new. But then you just start noticing patterns and it gets boring AF. No fun at all.

Played for a while hoping to get some game perks with XP gained (thought you gain skills once I saw what BOTs do - forget about it).
BOTs are magicians in this game. 

I appreciate that it's F2P game, but still... Gets really boring, as most of the time you play against bots and have no chance to experience real team work.

My advice - (if you want) install, play for few hours/enjoy until you can, uninstall.

Just be prepared to play against AI most of the time.

author: {'steamid': '76561198255150886', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 21, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 21, 'last_played': 1513628973}
review:
Overall seems fun. Not going to write what I liked, but rather few things that I didn't like (there's fewer of those so it's easier and everything else is quite positive).

1) Third person camera is soooooo much needed. From first person perspective it's sometimes hard to follow up on all the action. Rocket League (tbh, it's pretty impossible not to compare these two) did that excellent and I believe that it would bring such improvement here.

2) This is probably possible to adjust in the settings (I haven't really tweaked much there), but effects can sometimes make it hard to catch up on the play, so if there aren't already options to lower them or optimize it would be nice to add it up.

Like I said, all in all very sweet and action packed game and I'm certainly looking forward to the future improvements and development.

8.5/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198007269967', 'num_games_owned': 1092, 'num_reviews': 30, 'playtime_forever': 859, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 584, 'last_played': 1518932651}
review:
Gameplay is polished and fun and definitely has that "easy to learn, hard to master" kind of hook to it. 
Fantastically fun with a small group of people, lots of strategy and varied styles of play (not just how different it is to play goalie vs striker, but in terms of how you prefer to play those roles as well). 

Few minor gripes are a few annoying UI/gameplay bugs, but it really isn't anything gamebreaking. 

For free something like this can't really be beat.

author: {'steamid': '76561198178512273', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 45, 'playtime_forever': 176, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 148, 'last_played': 1522900806}
review:
This game for free you cant beat it. I was sceptical at first as i have over 400hrs in RL i was jadded of it and wanted something similar but less serious for casual play and here it its. Rather funny game to play and chellenging to learn the controls at first but I think this maybe Esporst material lol. 

Pros: Controls are well put together and pretty easy to learn after the tut and one match
         Good graphics - nothing to rediculious or over the top
         Gameplay is well thought out 

Cons: Not really anything i could find yet... After playing a little bit longer the community will be a drag as theres already asshole players in unranked getting salty because they lose or youre a new player not a con for the game but for the whole community


Suggestions: I would say a user interface could be a little bit better 
                      Character customization would be great! Accersories, Gun color, power up color, ect...
                      UPDATE: This game is addicting 

Great game and concept a must have in your library!

author: {'steamid': '76561198030637029', 'num_games_owned': 737, 'num_reviews': 180, 'playtime_forever': 156, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 156, 'last_played': 1512392755}
review:
Supra ball est un jeu indé de foot en FPS

le gameplay est nerveux et permet de mettre en place des stratégies diverses et variées ou des coup assez technique
la prise en main est relativement simple mais il faudra vite s'entrainer pour s'ameliorer.
le jeu permet de customisez ses perso 'on debloque des élément en gagnant des niveaux ou en achetant des loots box (le jeu est gratuit)
le jeu présente 13 maps (terrains classique en exterieur et interieur avec des météos variés, volcan, chateau, plage, lune...)
le style graphique est sympa sans être transcendant.

le jeu est délaisser par les joueurs 'principalement a cause des joueurs qui en peuvent s'empecher d'insulter les autres quand un match ne se déroule pas comme ils veulent. ormi cela le jeu à un potentiel bien réel!

https://youtu.be/9crK1UUPbow
