review:
This game is not worth your time!!! There is like 5 players who play this game and you get in the same game with same people all the time. Tip for new players: How I go lvl 6 with 2 hours? I just invited my friend to the same team and we passed each other for the rest of the game. There was no opponents so we got lvl 6 very fast!!! NB: use long passes and 5v5 map. One more thing- dont score before time runs out because the game goes to overtime, that way you can earn more exp. I was so happy when I reached lvl 6 only passing with my friend for 2 constitutive hours. Then we wanted to play ranked... but it turned out that nobody plays that shi* and we never had a chance to play ranked game. Then I wanted to have some fun and speedhacked. Eventually I got ban. 
10/10 would hack again!
Ohh one more thing, never buy chests and keys they are not worth it. Ty for your attention.

review: É um jogo simples, com um conceito juvenil, mas com uns gráficos muito refinados. Esteticamente, só peca por excesso de brilho e no bloom hdr. Quanto à gameplay, claro está, é bastante infantil, e pode ter um modo de jogo estranho, e ser excessivamente fictício. No entanto, acredito que exista uma grande margem de jogadores interessados neste tipo de conteúdo. Não posso dizer que recomendo, nem que não recomendo. Não faz a minha preferência, apesar de que acredito que tenha uma audiência específica. Posto isso, recomendo.

author: {'steamid': '76561198066101085', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 13329, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 627, 'last_played': 1647726284}
review:
This game is amazing! the graphics are great which make this game available to a lot of people with low/mid computer quality. This is game has everything it needs to be one of the best games in this genere. It has an amazing developers who upgrades the game and surprise the community every time again and again and again.
The game's objective is very simple like in football to score the other team's goal. There are different of things that the developers added to the game like dash, types of jumps (normal, x2,x3,x4), the ability to curve the ball and of course the power of the shoot with a meter. 
The tutorial is great, Its very easy to learn the basics and even some advance things. the gameplay is such great, the game is smooth and it very fun to play it.
I can see very bright future to this game, if the developers continue work and make a lot of updates like they do every month (and even more than once in a month) and if the base players will grow then I even can see the game as a popular competetive eSport like CSGO, DOTA, League of Legends and more games that you might know.
I recommend you all to play this game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198140557223', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 15119, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5295, 'last_played': 1566908855}
review:
So to start this game is free and is short to download so just check it out.
 
Pros:
-You can get matches very quickly.
-Teamwork is needed to win.
-No hackers.
-This game requires some skill and is not that easy to master.
-Very fun.
-Even more fun with friends.
-Strategies are needed to beat advanced players.
-Majority of players are 'cool'
-The bots are fairly descent to play with.
-Graphics may not be that impressive but are smooth and don't require a advanced graphics card.
-Tutorial is good gives the basics but not the full game away.

Cons:
-Some very minor glitches that are extremely rare.

Overall this game is one of the best ive played  the gameplay is very fun and is always interesting.

review:
Garbage game. 

Ball moves like a bowling ball. 

You have health for some reason and enemies can knock you out but you can't knock them out? 

Forget jump catches, the ball passes through you. 

The pull is such short range that it doesn't even matter. 

Shooting full power the ball still drops  1 foot for every 10 feet traveled. 

Players randomly boost you for no reason. 

Shots at the goal even if they are inside the rails still hit the rails.  

The tutorial is weird, coins unexplained, cannot do advanced parts of tutorial.

0/10 Just play rocket league.

author: {'steamid': '76561198324841815', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 49, 'playtime_forever': 81, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 81, 'last_played': 1506226598}
review: 괜찮은 게임이다. 하이퍼 스포츠 fps라 해야한다. 다양한 맵들이 존재한다. 다만 트레일러는 빠른 템포의 경기를 보여주지만 실제 게임을 들어가면 비슷한 실력의 유저들과 매칭되기에 서로 느릿한 분위기가 만들어질 수 있는것이 단점이다.(초보들이라) 이 게임에서 공을 받으면 공이 캐릭터에 흡수된다는 것이 매우 신박했다. 그리고 그것을 보완하기위해 공을 가지고 있는 유저를  기절시킬 수 있어 서로에게 공평한 경기를 만든다. 결론은 밸런스가 나쁘지 않게 잘 잡혀있고 페이투 윈과 아이템마다의 능력치 차인는 존재하지 않아 연습만 하면 누구나 프로가 될수 있다.(그래도 팀원들이 못받쳐주면 못한다;;)어쨋든 신박한 일인칭게임을 경험하게되어 기쁘다.원래 유료게임이었던 슈프라볼이 무료화되며 모두가 체험해볼 수 있게 되었다. 이 기회로 사람들이 늘어났으면 좋겠다.

author: {'steamid': '76561198188880637', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 721, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 705, 'last_played': 1507503860}
review:
First of all, i don't get the hate that this game got the first time. Sure it was not finished, there were some bug here and there and not many players to play against or with. But at the time i really can say that this game got GREAT! No more bugs, an almost unlimited amount of players and hours of fun! Almost every week there are some updates for this game which fix little bugs or add new stuff!

If we talk about Pay to Win, there is no such thing in this game. The only things you can buy with real money are chests and keys. Those drop (like in csgo) four random items taken randomly from the common, uncommon, rare, epic and legendary tiers. For example, my favourite item is the Mankini! There are also many hats and caps and items i didn't discover yet. As you can see there are really many items to collect!

The Developers work day in and day out to create a game that is as near to perfect as possible. DavidM, the Game Designer, supports the game in his free time by playing the game and helping Newbies out. He teaches them tricks or tactics or answers them questions about this game. So, if you see him InGame, don't be shy to ask him about help!

At the end i only can say that it's a great game and that i recommend that you should check it out. If you like the game, support the developers by buying crates or reporting bugs!

Regards

author: {'steamid': '76561198079156598', 'num_games_owned': 140, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 641, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 474, 'last_played': 1606695962}
review:
As mentioned 1000's of times in the review section, at first look Supraball could very easily be compared to Rocket League but in practice they play very differently.
In my (admitedly limited) experience in both games, Rocket League has a much heavier focus on solo play and technical finesse, whilst Supraball is much more about the interaction with your teammates and enemies.
This is not to say that technical skill is a non-factor to Supraball, at the time of writing the review I have 6.1hours played and I think I have learned just about enough to know what I don't know.
The gameplay itself has a low barrier to entry but high level of mastery, the 'auto'-pass function makes getting to grips with the game very manageable and makes you and at least a minimally effective player whilst you're getting your bearings.

Pros:
- The game is free-to-play, doesn't have huge spec requirements and does not take up much space at all on the HDD. I see no reason at all for not at least giving the game a try.
- There is huge room for personal improvement, you can play game after game and keep learning and gain new insights each time.
- The mechanics of the game are hugely fun and rewarding. All the basic interactions can be built upon and exploited to high levels to create high coordination, challenging plays.
- The tutorial island explains the gameplay a step at a time and lets you familiarise yourself with gameplay before diving in, provided you don't accidentally skip parts of the tutorial.
- Bots have impressive AI which actually does not leave a lot to be desired, although the real fun in this game is in playing with a full team.
- Pathing calculations for auto-passing are way better than I had expected and the function never feels clunky.
- There is a YT series of tutorial videos which are very good at expounding on what you learned from tutorial island.
- After match EXP/Stats breakdowns are always weirdly satisfying to peruse over.

Neutral :
- UI/Launcher/Lobby are very embryonic and basic but they do everything you need.
- Playerbase isn't the largest, but really all you need are two friends to have a team for 3v3's, and with the low requirements to play the game it shouldn't be too hard to get a couple other people on to play with.
- There is a cosmetic system (chest and key microtransactions), personally I am never here nor there for cosmetic features in any game, in Supraball the inventory/unlocking is very basic along with its UI but the implementation in-game is very well done.

Cons :
- There is a sound effect when a match is found and I have yet to find a good way of adjusting the volume of that so I don't get RIP'd as a headphone user. (I'm probably missing out on something obvious that can easily fix this issue though.)
- Mostly it really, if you don't enjoy the game you've lost nothing.

Conclusion:
I am deeply enjoying this game and have played it over Rocket League [as I feel both games are suited to playing 15-30 sessions] every time, gameplay is really fun and its a very accessible game to get other players into.
If you're already reading the review section there is no reason not to download and play at least a couple games.
The caveats are down to the fact that game is in Early Access and early development, although gameplay does not feel unpolished at all.

author: {'steamid': '76561197993780939', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 3332, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1484, 'last_played': 1550168681}
review:
Considering its early access status, Supraball is well polished and has a very decent tutorial to get new players up to speed. I was a huge fan of the games previous incarnation 'Deathball' and played in the leagues back in the day. I look forward to the ranked play in the future and seeing where the game expands to.

The gameplay is smooth, the grahics are clear and the UI is not over-cluttered with screen furniture. It's just you, the teams and the ball as it should be.

The basic techniques of play are easy to pick up but obviosuly there are skills and other tricky moves to learn and perfect. The learning curve is not too steep though and once you get the hang of jump-boosting and rebound goals it is a very fun, rewarding game with friends and on your own in random teams too.

It's good to see you back DavidM.

author: {'steamid': '76561198137803102', 'num_games_owned': 203, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 325, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 173, 'last_played': 1568822169}
review:
Despite being not really polished, that does not mean fun cannot be gained.

Played it several times with friends, and I would love to say that we enjoyed it.
I can't say anything more than fun, but we do have a problem.

We kept getting matchmaking issue with a party. It's so hard get any matches, it's like 1 in a 10 chance. And once we got in, we were playing with bots (this is probably has something to do with the playerbase, instead of the game).

And the bots, despite being really good at some points, felt like too dumbed down and ridiculous at the same time. You run faster than the bots, which is a nice thing to have, but made it too easy. The bots always do long passes that's guaranteed will never miss, means we'd literally have to wait them to shoot to the goal and let the keeper catch it instead of intercepting, which is really hard.

Another thing is, I have a crappy laptop. Despite having the lowest settings, it still noticably lags, especially in the snow arena. Pls fix.

However, despite these issue, the game is already a solid piece of entertainment value.
Would play with friends again.

author: {'steamid': '76561197963837127', 'num_games_owned': 165, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 5337, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4763, 'last_played': 1546554351}
review:
Ihr wolltet schon immer mal eine Mischung aus Unreal Tournament und Fußball spielen? Dann ist das hier genau das richtige Spiel für euch :)

Worum geht es?
Wie beim Fußball geht es darum Tore zu schiessen und auch die Arenen sind mehr oder weniger ein Klassisches Fußballfeld. Gespielt wird 3v3 oder 5v5. Wenn man sich für das Solo Spiel anmeldet wird einem eine position zugeteilt. Torwart - defensives Mittelfeld oder offensives Mittelfeld. Die Position sollte man auch einhalten sonst artet alles etwas in Chaos aus. Was erfreulicherweise aber zu 90% wunderbar klappt.

Bei dem Spiel ist Teamplay gefragt im alleingang kommt ihr hier nicht weit und es macht auch nicht so besonders viel Spaß wenn alle nur sinnlos durch die Gegend bolzen. Aber mit ein paar Freunden macht das ganze mega Laune.
Die Community ist super nett und Hilfsbereit somit findet man auch ganz schnel ein paar Mitspieler. ( Macxht aber auch spaß wenn man sich solo fürs match anmeldet )

Die Steuerung ist am anfang ein wenig überfordernd aber nach ein paar Runden hat man die Grundlagen eigentlich raus. Dabei ist das Tutorial ganz hilfreich und auch die Videos auf der Homepage der Entwickler. Für die ganz abgefahrenen Tricks muss man dann einfach mal bei youtube reinschauen.

Kann das Spiel absolout empfehlen es macht wirklich einfach nur tierisch Spaß :)

Bin kein professioneller Review schreiber also sind mir die Rechtschreibfehler egal :P

review:
Awesome little game. The fun is real even if some players are toxic like in all game. The gameplay is simple to begin with, but with time and practice (tutorial help) you can do some awesome move. There is some rewards (skin and chest) from time to time, so it's great.
The game's duration is quite small but intense, just the amount of time to get fun.
The graphisms are quite simple but effective, the sound is nice, but sadly no music. The interface is not easy to understand, I think a better interface could be great.

But the more fun : the knockout!! If a player has the ball you can beat him to the unconsciousness, ahahah !!!

Anyway, it's Free2Play, so grab the game and get in the field.

review:
Meglepően jó játék. A szerver néha tud fura dolgokat produkálni, és sajnos a csapattársak sincsenek mindig a helyzet magaslatán (például amikor a kapus meg a védő a teljes támadóidőt végigpasszolgatja, majd a végén a kapus fellövi az égbe a labdát 3v3-ban, az nagyon idegesítő tud lenni). De mivel ingyenes, és abszolút nem pay to win, ezért bátran merem ajánlani bárkinek, aki valami újdonságra vágyik.

Ha ügyes vagy, akkor egészen elképesztő dolgokat tudsz csinálni a játékban, érdemes utánanézni YouTube-on, hogy mire képesek a jobb játékosok.

author: {'steamid': '76561198052173722', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 56, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 56, 'last_played': 1504811715}
review:
tutorial made me ragequit instantly - controls are convoluted and do not respond well at all, to the point where you're finishiong most of the totorial missions by pure luck, and for the final challenge not even that - pitted against an AI you can't manage to defend the goal against to finish the challenge of blocking 8 shots. 
The opponents shots beyond a vague sound indication when they let go of their shot, are impossible to predict, since the ball can be influenced to travel along a certain path while firing, defending the goal eight times is doable, but having the counter reset each time you let one pass is more of a pain then it's worth, and made me want to do actual physical harm to whomever designed this 'challenge'.

At the end of it all i was left with a raised blood pressure and the experience was just not fun - and that's what i'm looking for in a game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198152418161', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 170, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 90, 'last_played': 1621711201}
review:
[h1]Supraball-gutes spiel jetzt auch kostenlos[h1]
Ich hatte mir überlegt das spiel zu kaufen der Preis lag bis vor kurzem noch bei 9.99€ doch nun ist das Spiel kostenlos und ich habe es mir gleich heruntergeladen! Das spiel ist sowohl vom Gamplay als auch von der Grafik sehr Überzeugend! Der PC muss auch nicht der Beste sein! Es reicht ein i3-7100 und eine gtx 1050ti um das spiel in den höchsten einstellungen mit 60fps zu genißen! Wenn mann nicht so einen gutes PC hat sollte man die Grafik runterschrauben! Mann finded immer ein Spiel und muss nie warten bis mann dazu kommt! Es gibt auch kein pay to win! Jeder Spieler hat die gleichen Berechtigungen

-Gameplay 9/10 "Gut aber manchmal noch kleine Kamera Fehler"
-Grafik 10/10 "sieht wirklich gut aus, selbst die Zuschauer bewegen sich"
-Gestaltungsfreiheit 7/10 "es bietet einem schon mehr möglichkeiten seine Figur anzupassen, es währe aber schön wenn 
 mann eine Hose ein Skin ein Shirt und Harre wählen könnte, denn somit hätte mann mehr optionen sich zu gestalten!"

Sonstige anmerkungen: - es wäre vielleicht schon den Skin der Ballkanone zu wechseln!

FAZIT: Gutes Spiel jetzt auch kostenlos, auf jedenfall zu empfehlen!

author: {'steamid': '76561197972110435', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 3, 'playtime_forever': 38086, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 36269, 'last_played': 1556330368}
review:
This game is extremely addicitve.  The rush that you get when scoring or saving a goal is incredible.   Teamwork is very important (boosting, passing, defending, etc).  While the gist of the game is simple, there are enough controls to really allow a player to develop thier own style.  

My biggest complaints with the game at this stage of development, are the small playerbase, and the matchmaking, but now that the game is F2P, I'm hoping that those items will be resolved!  The devs are open to suggestions with the interface, and I think once more players start coming to the game, the interface and matchmaking will get some updates.

Definitely recommend giving the game a try, epesically if you like games like Rocket League.  The level of control is far greater here.

author: {'steamid': '76561198129136200', 'num_games_owned': 152, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 801, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 482, 'last_played': 1509889132}
review:
Supraball is convincing with this very cool game idea of playing football in first-person with a gun. I think its not the only first-person football game, but Supraball makes much more fun with its own rules. Especially these many abilities you have as a player with your shild. You can score amazing volley goals, give your ball a tricky spin, do impressive passplays with your teammates and knockout your opponents. The gameplay feels very good as well, the controls via keyboard and mouse are very precise and easy to learn. Beside the gameplay, there is a really good matchmaking and lobby system and also a lot customization abilities for your player. After a game you receive very extensive statistics about your game.

I don't had a game before, which made me having that much fun. So I really recommend you this game, take a look at it!

I hope, I'll see you ingame soon.
Have fun!

review: You know, I remember getting early access for this game back in 2016, but it never really took off. With few players and some shotty servers I thought this game went down the gutter even though I saw so much potential in it. But, now the game is free, which I believe is a good move if you want to grow your main player base. And I feel that the gameplay has  improved substancially, partly because there are people playing, but overall it does feel smoother. So I do recommend that everyone at least try this game. Grab a couple friends and start a team. 20/10 would Supraball again.

review:
Supraball is the successor to deathball and a superior product for coordinated team sports action. I'd recommend this for anyone who is willing to take steps to be a team player and enjoy the game for love of the art of a genre that needs more exploration.

It's inspired many and deserves its due. 

It's free to play now, you can enjoy everything about the game without paying a cent. If you enjoy it. Get a key set yourself apart from the pack.

Enjoy mates good times ahead!

author: {'steamid': '76561198087339199', 'num_games_owned': 281, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 5086, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 5017, 'last_played': 1504387782}
review:
Hakettiği ilgiyi göremeyen harika bir spor oyunu.

Oyun fps bir futbol oyunu. Elinizde bir silah var ve tüm aksiyonları bu silahla yapıyorsunuz. Topu alma, şut vurma, top çıkarma gibi. 

Oyunun eski oyuncuları çok iyi oynadıkları için yeni başlarken sıkıntı yaşıyorsunuz. Oynadıkça bu farkı aşabiliyorsunuz bu yüzden çok pratik gerekiyor.

Geliştirici ekip sürekli oyunla haşır neşir hatta oyunlara girip oynuyorlar. Bu nedenle hatalar çabuk düzeltiliyor.

Tek eksiği oyuncu sayısı. Az oyuncu olduğu için maçlara girmek uzun sürüyor. İlerde F2P yapmayı düşündükleri için bu sıkıntı da aşılacak gibi.

author: {'steamid': '76561198010560368', 'num_games_owned': 1183, 'num_reviews': 703, 'playtime_forever': 289, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 289, 'last_played': 1485984641}
review: Интересная идея реализовать футбол в качестве шутера, где мы ловим мяч специальной пушкой и потом со всей дури выстреливаем по воротам. Сейчас вообще модно включать футбол во все что угодно, та же успешная Rocket League, где вместо футболистов выступают машины. Возвращаясь к Supraball, мы видим проблему в лице мертвого онлайна, что делает ее невозможной для игры.

author: {'steamid': '76561198241938368', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 7, 'playtime_forever': 1174, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1174, 'last_played': 1515260789}
review:
The greatest mystery is why this game isn't popular yet. 

The only explanation that can make sense is that this game is too complex for the type of gamer who just installs and play. Few are those willing to read, watch, and learn before playing. Maybe if it started as a simple game and got complex with time by adding features, it would have worked out.
This unpopular game has one of the highest skill caps in the gaming industry and this was the case from the beginning due to the wide variety and availability of its features. Because it had no publicity, this game started with low player base and continued in the same fashion. Why? Because high skill cap means huge gap in skill between the players. Add to this the low amount of player base and you get extremely unbalanced matches that will either make you quit or uninstall but keep this game on your radar to monitor the player base.

author: {'steamid': '76561198119546696', 'num_games_owned': 138, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 6772, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3145, 'last_played': 1612026783}
review:
---------- English --------------

This game is awesome, I highly recommand it !
Despite of the percentage of very experimented players, and the lack of players in general, this game have a huge potential, especially with the incomming Free 2 Play and the creation of many servers around the world.
Developers recently added outfits dropable in-game witch can help funding the future F2P and servers.
In short, developers are fully engaged into the game expansion and are listening to the players community

---------- Français --------------

Ce jeu est vraiment très bien, je le recommande !
Malgré le pourcentage de joueurs très expérimentés, et le manque de joueurs en général, ce jeu a un grand potentiel, surtout compte-tenu du Free 2 Play à venir et la création de nombreux serveurs partout dans le monde.
Les développeurs ont récemment implémenté des tenues à obtenir en jouant au jeu ( drop de skins ), ce qui peut aider au financement futur du F2P et des serveurs.
En bref, les développeurs sont à fond dans l'expansion du jeu et sont à l'écoute des joueurs.

author: {'steamid': '76561198276306343', 'num_games_owned': 112, 'num_reviews': 25, 'playtime_forever': 4019, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 923, 'last_played': 1585674954}
review:
Играл в эту игру тогда, в далеком 2014-2015, когда ее еще не было в стиме. За это время разработчики мало чего поменяли в игре.

Из самого противного в игре я хочу отметить лаунчер, это ну просто убожество, оно ужасно неудобное. Я три минуты искал как начать матч с онлайн игроками. Этот лаунчер можно было не создавать, а встроить прямо в игру (меню), как в той же Рокет Лиге или других играх. 
Так же игра очень сыра и требует дальнейших конкретных доработок. 
Было бы еще интересно увидеть в игре другие различные режимы игры. 

Но все траблы этой игры перекрывает ее динамичность и красота, игра сделана в своем оригинальном стиле с интересным геймплеем. В этой игре часто победа команды зависит от самой команды. Так же не может не радовать выпадение различного шмота который можно надеть на своего персонажа, либо продать на торговой площадке.

Всех любителей командной игры и динамичности - советую к покупке!)

author: {'steamid': '76561198045268025', 'num_games_owned': 250, 'num_reviews': 61, 'playtime_forever': 315, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 138, 'last_played': 1525573661}
review:
This game has insane potential for competitive and esport gameplay. If you buy the game now, you will see empty servers and likely will be stuck playing against and with bots. It is widely understood that the game will be going free to play within the next month, so if you are interested in playing Supraball I suggest you wait until then.

People who want to play the game (despite having to put in extra effort to find a community to play with in the game's current low population state) are the people who should be purchasing the game now.

Supraball is a solid competitive experience, those who are giving the game negative reviews right now do not understand that the developers are not ready to support a big playerbase. They buy the game expecting a finished product, when in reality they are buying a copy of a game that is not intended to be played by the masses. When the developers have decided that the game is ready, Supraball will go free to play and those who focus on the game's low population as a reason to leave a negative review will be welcome.

author: {'steamid': '76561198381183489', 'num_games_owned': 104, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 886, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 341, 'last_played': 1697878290}
review:
We NEED Asian server PLEASE!!!

首先作为一款FPS足球游戏，整个画面和视角还是很不错的，很舒服。
游戏操作性很强，但是操作方式十分简洁。
整体操作难度个人感觉偏高（比如我右键就没吸到过球），得多加练习才能上手。

有几个不足之处：
1.FPS太高……敢联机就敢放幻灯片
2.每次打人机，唤醒AI的时间真的好长好长
3.Beginner难度的AI智商太低……打一局80%的进球都是回传守门失误

总之是款挺不错的游戏，挺值得期待的。希望正式版能够更好

author: {'steamid': '76561198008549198', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 576, 'playtime_forever': 386, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 386, 'last_played': 1497423444}
review:
I received it as a gift, so I really wanted to give this game a fair chance, but this is a tough game:

1) no ranking system so you get matched up against nolifers who have been playing the game for years

2) the controls are not fully rebindable: notably the shift and control keys seem hard wired to their functions, meaning I'll often hit them both at the same time by accident, switching my keyboard back and forth between qwerty and azerty, fucking me in the process

3) sometimes the controls just don't respond. I was once stuck with the ball, not being able to throw it until of course I got beaten up. That's right, beaten up, it claims to be a football game but if you ask me it's more of a wrestling game.

4) sometimes in matches where most players are bots, for some reason the bots will have different level in the 2 teams, potentially leaving you at a HUGE disadvantage


I'll still try to get an achievement later I guess...... almost got the "don't get beaten up" one last time, until I had that bug where I couldn't get rid of the damn ball :x

Edit: well once you get used to it, and if you're lucky enough not to encounter the bug in my point 3, it gets a bit more enjoyable. I'll still leave the negative rating because it's highly unpolished, but it's not too bad after all.

author: {'steamid': '76561197989305939', 'num_games_owned': 213, 'num_reviews': 28, 'playtime_forever': 67296, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 45824, 'last_played': 1675205421}
review:
I played supraball for +3 years. This game had a huge potential in Alpha version. Servers were filled all nights, people were playing to play.
When they launched the pre-beta, more than 50% people left.

Pros : 
- Simple design
- Huge potential gameplay
- Difficult vs experimented players

cons : 
- Til' bêta, community is cancer
- Developping is very slow and dev team doesn't hear community at all
- Too much bugs, there were not that much in Alpha...
- No ppl to play with actually

If you want to play this game, wait for the free2play. 

I've donated 50€ during crowdfunding in late alpha (like some guys too), we had skins for this. And you know what ? They just removed them. OK. 1st TWAT.
2nd TWAT : They removed ranked games so everyone can play with beginners, good idea on the paper. BUT ! Why the fuck do you create PUG servers where only veterant will go ? The goal wasn't for everyone to play with beginners ? resulting : no one plays on matchmaking, they just regroup on pug servers and beginners play 1-2 hrs then leave forever. 

I used to be a fan of this game, but now it's done, i'm gone. This game is dead atm, don't expect anything for the moment.

Edit 1 (dd/mm/yyyy) 06/07/2017 : Finally, they gave back the crowdfounders skins we paid for, also working on the last skins remainings for those. Dev team could have been tell if they needed to remove them temporarly, it would prevent such bad reviews, or atleast, some bad points in reviews.

author: {'steamid': '76561198081580561', 'num_games_owned': 46, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 202050, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 60767, 'last_played': 1708882427}
review:
This game is great.
It's very alive, with such a great community open to help new players.
DavidM, the head developer, is a great human being, he helped me to pass through hard moments of life and he actually became my best friend.
I enjoy the weekly updates that improve constantly the game, and i have no doubt that this game will soon become an esport.
I never met a bug in more than 3000 hours of ACTIVE playtime, ranked games are something special, probably best challenge you will ever find in a multiplayer.
Sometimes you could meet some very good players that i would recommend you to carefully observe, to learn something fency and great, like Cathode or Mihr.
I recommend you to try this game as soon as possible, to taste every single piece of it, no need to thank me.
Enjoy Supraball, enjoy life.

author: {'steamid': '76561198111145366', 'num_games_owned': 1082, 'num_reviews': 79, 'playtime_forever': 513, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 339, 'last_played': 1647876623}
review:
Marrant. Jeu en équipe oú il n'y a personne pour parler stratégie.
Bref, faut ce dépatouiller.
En jouant basiquement, on peut pas mal jouer mais contre ceux qui maitrisent on prend la misère.

Pas d'histoire ni de contexte. On joue c'est tout.
Graphismes des joueurs basiques. Les étendues autours du terrain de jeu sont par contre belles et lointaines... allez comprendre.

author: {'steamid': '76561198116180406', 'num_games_owned': 1995, 'num_reviews': 45, 'playtime_forever': 294, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 294, 'last_played': 1491772257}
review:
Игра совсем не динамичная, скучная, однобокая и явно не дотягивает до полноценной киберспортивной дисциплины, какой ее хотят увидеть разрабы и фанаты. Неудобное игровое меню, которое находится ВНЕ игры, долгие загрузки, ненужная заставка, неполноценная графика в сумме с отсутствующей оптимизацией.
Игра нисколько не окупает цены, которая ей выставлена в Steam.
2/10 за старания

author: {'steamid': '76561198053478305', 'num_games_owned': 3246, 'num_reviews': 129, 'playtime_forever': 4187, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 596, 'last_played': 1513865696}
review:
Game is dead, or the playerbase rather.
You need a minimum of 6 players to even start a game, and I've never seen more than 3...

Edit

Found the dev in a lobby and after we played a match (took forever to get in) he suggested I shouldn't try to join lobbies but rather go for matchmaking instead.
Altho it took 10 minutes for me to get in a game (which made me go to lobbies before), the matches after started right away. My suggestion or rather from the dev would be to not look in the server browser but just go for matchmaking right away and enjoy the game for what it is.

Glad to see a dev this concerned with his product and looking forward to the updates.

author: {'steamid': '76561198041382438', 'num_games_owned': 194, 'num_reviews': 16, 'playtime_forever': 268, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 166, 'last_played': 1516052510}
review:
La storia è questa... ai tempi di Unreal Tournamento 2003 e 2004 esistevano diverse mod più o meno conosciute, una di queste si chiamava Deathball ed era giocatissima da una ristretta cerchia di persone, perchè o piaceva o non piaceva e a differenza del vero e proprio UT, qui contava solo il gioco di squadra, quindi difficilmente chi provava la mod tanto per, poi rimaneva... Cercate "deathball mod" su YouTube.

Gli stessi sviluppatori di quella mod, ora stanno sviluppando Supraball quindi posso chiudere anche qui la recensione con la garanzia che il gioco verrà uno spettacolo.

Per tutto coloro che lasceranno la classica e solita recensione in cui si evidenziano esclusivamente i bug, è inutile ricordare ch siamo in Early Access, quasi ogni giorno i dev rilasciano novità su Discord, stanno lavorando costantemente. Per ora il gioco rimane acerbo, non ancora pronto per essere apprezzato e gustato da chiunque, ma solo dai veri fan che già ci giocano e organizzano tornei. Forse i 10€ sembrano troppi... ma sappiate che acquistando il gioco non fate altro che supportarlo nel vero senso del termine, in quanto quando sarà rilasciato, sarà free-to-play come lo era la mod di UT.

author: {'steamid': '76561198233572100', 'num_games_owned': 13, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 75243, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 69800, 'last_played': 1706614008}
review:
Postive:

Competive
Ranked
Teams
Easy to understand but hard to master
Art Style (opinion based)
Customizables


Negative:

Terrible optimisation
Networking is trash
The launcher is from the mid 90's seems like
Ranked is currently disabled
Not enough players
Developers have no vision of what is happening inside the community
Even with freetoplay nobody is playing it
Unbalanced gameplay, a midfielder can't beat a defender one on one. Walls are inconsictent and this has been for over 3 years.
Alot of players are toxic
Sometimes when you use a name with symbols, the master server won't allow you in.
Banning the best player because they give building critisism
Developers are ignorant
Game sometimes randomly crashes
Not enough volume options
Annoying sunsets disabling the view of the pitch
Only 3 maps are usable for competive play, the other ones you need to adjust your brighitness otherwise it will burn out your eyes.



TLDR:

Don't play it. The negative points compared to the positive points doesn't balance it. Developers won't asnwer your mails if you have questions.

Wait after early acces.

review: Gioco bello e con una bella idea dietro, molto innovativa. Unici contro che ho trovato sono stati due: Il prezzo e il numero di giocatori. 10 euro a parer mio, sono troppi, dato che pochi spendono tale cifta per un gioco che ancora è in fase di sviluppo. Da questo problema, deriva anche il secondo ovvero il numero d'utenza, che effettivamente lascia un pò perplessi.Il numero di players è appunto calato drasticamente dalla versione alpha gratuita del gioco. Tutta via, altri contro non ho trovato e consiglio questo gioco, soprattutto se in sconto.

author: {'steamid': '76561198038276571', 'num_games_owned': 322, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 1392, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1153, 'last_played': 1482886395}
review:
This game is marvelous and needs more attention from the players on steam! The skill ceiling is off the roof for the start of my review. If you have a tight buddy group of 5 or more just buy it eyes closed you will have a sh.. load of fun for sure. And the "Masters of Gravity" will give your eyes a feast. I mean like 360 swirling volley shots is the best :o

Pros:
-Hell of a fun
-Learning the game mechanics is not hard at all but its hard to master.
-Great graphics/effects/movement for this kind of a game
-Sound design is marvelous
-Matches are long but you will not understand when its finished cause its fast paced
-No bugs as far as I've seen
-Great Training Rooms for understanding the basic/medium/hard moves
-And the secret :>

Cons: (I assume these will go away till the game is released)
-Player base is not big (yet) therefore the que times a bit long. (BUT it will be shortened when the game is recognized for sure)
-MM is not that good right now because I'm a fresh blood and im matching with "MoG" (and again I'm saying YET)
-The knockout mechanic is good but the time you are knocked out is a bit long imo (YET again :P)
-Connected to the knockout mechanic the "hit punch" from the hits are too disorienting for the new players ( and YET again)

This is my honest review right now and the Dev. is a gentlemen for sure he did not let any of my questions unanswered. Just buy this game you will not regret it at all!

review:
This game, it quickly became one of, if not, my favourite game back in the alpha stage 2 years ago. It's easy to learn but very hard to master, in fact, no one has even come close to mastering it yet. But don't let that scare you, after training and just playing around with friends for a little bit, when you become a little more adapted and better at the game, you will get addicted, it is a ton of fun. [b]Magyar:[/b]El lehet vicceskedni ha arról van szó, magába szív a játék. A legrosszabb dolog a játékba sajnos az alacsony játékosszám. Legtöbbször 8 óra megtölteni egy rangsorolt meccskeresést. A jó benne az, ha miután 1 játék lement, utána még sok követi. Később biztos élvezetesebb lesz több emberrel, most igazából a profi meccsekben mindenki ismer mindenkit, már majdnem előre tudjuk a végét. Végsősorban egy próbát megér, úgyis ingyenes.

author: {'steamid': '76561198170297379', 'num_games_owned': 97, 'num_reviews': 16, 'playtime_forever': 1004, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 552, 'last_played': 1555701043}
review:
NOTA: Abajo teneis mi analisis de cuando el juego era de pago, que es negativa.

Hace unos dias decidi volver a Supraball y por ahora me está transmitiendo las sensaciones de cuando iba a jugarlo por primera vez. Si quereis un análisis mas en profundidad mirar el de abajo, porque simplemente quiero decir que la comunidad, aunque sigue sin ser grande (como mucho 150 jugadores al dia) mola jugar con ella, aunque sigue habiendo algunos "chupones" y bastantes que van a saco por la pelota, pero la inclusión de bots si faltan personas (muy bien hechos los bots por cierto) y la mejoría de la comunidad y el juego en sí lo vuelve a hacer divertido.

Por ultimo, quiero resaltar el gran trabajo de los desarrolladores, que escuchan a la comunidad, se preocupan por ella y, aunque el desarrollo del juego este terminado y tienen al tambien buen juego SupraLand, siguen preocupándose por este.

Aqui teneis el analisis antiguo:

Mis primeras inmpresiones de este juego son, decepcionantemente malas. Vamos a empezar por este analisis.


Pille el juego gratis de una pagina, por eso no me voy a quejar tanto. Este juego es la hostia, la idea es muy buena y esta bien ejecutada, pero hay un gran fallo que lo echa todo al fuego:la comunidad. 10€ para esta comunidad, que ahora explicare, es un completo timo, pero ya sabeis esa pagina que patrocinan tantos youtubers, no?

La Comunidad:
Es una basura. El primer punto malo es que, ATENCION: Solo juegan unos 20 al dia, UNOS 20 al dia. De ahí, solo se puede decir a favor, que los partidos normalmente son de 3vs3, no de 5v5 que esta disponible. Si me dijeras que la comunidad es buena y te echas partidazos.....pero es que son chupones: no pasan, hacen trucos que tu no sabes y que te dejaran sentado y nockeado, para luego quejarse y expulsarte de la unica sala que esta ocupada a esa hora. Supondreis que habra bots, no? bueno, os lo dire mas adelante.

Modos de juego (Posibilidades de empezar a jugar):

Para dejarlo claro: no hay bots (Solo online). Con el juego abierto ahora mismo: Tienes launcher y donde pone play  te saldran estas opciones traducidas por mi al español: Tutorial, practica online, partido, competitivo(aun no lo he probado), tutorales en videos y buscador de servers. Bueno pues de esta lista solo quedaros con el tutorial y el buscador, lo demas es inutil,porque? pues es un matchmaking rapido pero impreciso, MUY impreciso. El tutorial es un buen punto a favor: entrenas habilidades desde las mas basicas hasta las imposibles, como pases con bots, tiros, porteria.....Y de lo demas es todo lo mismo, no penseis que son diferentes.

El juego en si: dentro de un partido "normal":

En si es basico: 2 equipos de 3 o 5 jugadores van con pistolas con las cuales pueden controlar una pelota, recuerda al rocket, aunque no se porque. Saques manuales y vueltas a tu campo manuales. Y posiciones libres, aunque antes del partido te pilles portero, pues salir sin ninguna desventaja, en cuanto entres en tu area te convertiras en portero si es que no habia otro antes, con lo cual no te podran dar y quitar la pelota. El click izquierdo carga potencia para disparar la pelota, y el derecho hace pases. Pues tirar con efecto incluso. Y todo este control hace que este juego sea uno de los mejores coop con el rocket, estar con 3 amigos e iros pasando la pelota y haciendo estrategias es divertido. Vamos en si el juego es muy bueno.

Futuro:

Lo que aun mantiene nuestra esperanza, el futuro. Y es que en estas navidades sacaran una gran actualizacion la cual traera bots y mucho mas. Y quien sabe: mas jugadores.


Ahora vamos finalizando, voy a dar unos consejos a los desarrolladores y os voy a decir cositas.

Desarrolladores, este juego se va a la mierda, y aunque el juego es bueno, se esta abandonando poco a poco, pero aun tiene 2 soluciones: la primera y de la que dependeran las dos en PUBLICIDAD. La 1ª constaria de ponerlo bien grande en las portadas de steam, poner el juego a 4 € como mucho y pagar a los youtubers cantidad para que promocionen a saco este juego, sino, de creeis que se dio a conocer el rocket, ese juego dio una buena publicidad para que la gente viera que habia un gran juego, vosotros teneis que hacer lo mismo, y tambien ponerlo gratis un finde, eso haria que el juego fuera a mejor. La 2ª y ultima opcion es tirar la toalla y ponerlo f2p, sino se puede hacer publicidad, hacer sin miedo este juego f2p, a los que pagan preferirian que hubiera mas gente de gratis a que tengan un juego al que no pueden jugar.




Y a los que leeis este analisis, por ahora le doy un no recomendado, tengo suerte de no haber pagado por este juego, modificare este analisis y seguire jugando hasta que saquen la actualizacion. En si, como digo el juego es un 9´3/10, pero la comunidad es  un 1/10. ¿Nota general? 4´4/10. Hasta luego.

author: {'steamid': '76561198064127671', 'num_games_owned': 371, 'num_reviews': 110, 'playtime_forever': 163, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 35, 'last_played': 1482663131}
review:
Идет топовый состав в поисках своих врагов,
Пиздюлей получат все - убегай раз не готов.
Вершину мало просто взять, ее надо удержать,
Пацаны шагают строем, чтобы это доказать.
 
Плотный строй, ровный ряд, сжаты кулаки, с опаской взгляд,
Шуршат кеды по пыльному асфальту, у кого-то сегодня будут танцы.
Сила каждого собирается в общую мощь,
Надобно не мало сил, чтоб это мощь превозмочь.
Тормозят машины, закрываются двери,
Состав сметает всё с пути, что мешает дойти до цели.
Оплеухи раздаются направо, налево,
Втоптать непрошеных гостей милое дело.
-Может ебнуть молодежь?
-Ты че гонишь? Эти спортики, этих не догонишь.
Как гром среди ясного неба прогремел заряд,
Какие-то типы у арки стоят.
Заряд в ответ, адреналин, зажглись дымы,
Собрались парни - это они.
 
Оппонентов больше - насрать!
Будет возможность проявить себя!
Имя фирмы любой ценой отстоять!
Не отступать! До конца стоять!


Игра конечно не про это. Вообще в ней все хорошо, приятная графика, физика, музыка и простота. жостаточно драйвовая. проблема в том, что людей нет. игра досталась нахаляву. но людей все-равно нет. почти нет. шанс сыграть 3 на 3 (не говоря 5 на 5) близок к нулю. Игру нужно делать бесплатной/снижать цену/делаить бесплатные выходные. А так, это очередная мертвая онлайновая годнота. Людей нет, но вы держитесь. купить и поиграть с друзьями, самое то.

author: {'steamid': '76561197999687465', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 63693, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 40587, 'last_played': 1679024898}
review:
I've played Supraball for about 3 years now. I'd say I probably spent ~1500 hours with it on the steam version and the versions before it. I can't recommend the game in its current state to anyone. Small playerbase (especially in north america) means you MAY get one game in a day if you're lucky. The dedicated community has all left, minus a few who still have hope. 

Devs should sell the game to a company with more resources. The actual gameplay is the same it's been for nearly 2 years. They've spent, somewhere around, the last year making the lobby system which, in its current state, is the last thing the game needs right now. At least they made a tutorial. But you won't be able to use the skills honed in tutorial in actual matches barely anyone plays the game anymore.

author: {'steamid': '76561198073876874', 'num_games_owned': 157, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 16601, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 9239, 'last_played': 1620872292}
review: This game is very enjoyable for those who like fps, but want something which doesn't nessesserily involve killing, more killing, and maybe even some objective play. In this game, you play football/handball from an fps camera view. I say bot football and handball because is half of each. I love this game to bits and higly recommend for anyone who wants to try something new and fun. This game also has a very competetive standpoint if you are a competetive player. Still very early access, so there are boudt to be glitches, and there are, but if you look away from that, it has much potential to become an amazing game. They are working on plentyfull of new updates as i am writing this, but as of right now, there are not many working on the game.

author: {'steamid': '76561198091013815', 'num_games_owned': 1462, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 1742, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 644, 'last_played': 1502456334}
review:
一人称アクションスポーツ

ルールはサッカーに似ていますがシールドやポータルガンのようなものを駆使しハイスピードな試合を展開します。
試合は5vs5と3vs3のみでBotは実装されていません（プラクティスモードなら人数が足りなくても遊べます）。
操作はシンプルでチュートリアルも充実していますが、全てのテクニックを使いこなすには相当な慣れが必要です。

ゲーム内容はとても面白く、うまく連携が取れるとものすごく気持ち良いです。
ですが残念なことに現在ほとんど人がいません…50人もいれば良いほうです。
もしフレンドを集めて遊べるのであればオススメします。

author: {'steamid': '76561198149677888', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 1548, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1317, 'last_played': 1537630901}
review:
this is an innovative game that cuold waste other sports games like fifa and pes. i hope it will get success. the weak point is that if you are not playing with your friends/squad you can't totally enjoy this game.
the toturial is well made and funny,and it is a good thing (there wasn't a tutorial before).
i think the experience for new player cuold be better by creating different "channels" for different levels of skill.
it cuold be the sport game of the future (also with the VR maybe?),it only needs some promotion.

author: {'steamid': '76561198236415554', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 61088, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 404, 'last_played': 1613582488}
review:
if you are looking for a fun and competitive game at the same time to play with friends, you can not find any better. The idea of the game is really innovative and very well made, with intuitive and simple controls, which generate a very fast and fun gameplay. The competitiveness is the strong point of this game, in fact you can do online matches where you try to win by using your and your team skill and strategies.
The graphics is very clean, pleasant and light. This makes the gameplay not stressful and without lag that can annoy.
I found no bugs in my first few hours and I am very satisfied.
Ultimately I hope that one day this game can go up to the levels of famous competitive online games, with international tournaments.
So I highly recommend it if you are looking for a competitive and fun game to play with friends.

author: {'steamid': '76561198020125851', 'num_games_owned': 15680, 'num_reviews': 840, 'playtime_forever': 706, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 585, 'last_played': 1482167495}
review:
[h1]A First Person Action Sports Game[/h1]
https://youtu.be/VzIQchsPE7g
+ The gameplay is a lot of fun. It's similar to Soccer, yet instead of kicking the ball you are shooting the ball out of a energy cannon or deflecting it with a shield. You are able to charge up your shots to shoot faster, and can do a variety of skillful passes and trickshots to make the goals. 
+ Visually the game looks great with some very nicely detailed graphics, lighting, and partical effects
+ Loads of various maps to play on with unique themes and sizes
+ The tutorial stage does a wonderful job of teaches you how to play in a interactive fun way. One of the best tutorials I've seen from a game.
+ Fast paced and exciting. It can feel very rewarding to launch a curve ball across the map and score a goal. 

[b]This game is in Early Access so don't take these too seriously[/b]
- Most of the populated servers seem to be EU based (or at least from what i've seen) which seemed to give me lag / very high ping. 
- I had issues with some of the controls. For example, right click allows you to scoop up or grab the ball from a distance, but at the same time right click also launches the ball. The problem with this is that your character will auto-pickup the ball if it touches you, so when a player passes the ball to you, you may think to right click to grab it, but you end up mistakingly launching the ball. When you are a goalie, you can press shift to dash back and fourth, and ctrl to put up a shield. The problem with this is that it's hard to press shift and ctrl quickly to move and deflect a ball.
- High Skill Gap / Learning Curve.... this game requires a LOT of practice, and tutorial videos if you want to get good. Unfortunetely as a noob, I experienced players wanting to kick me due to lack of experience. 
- No bots, this is bad because if no one is online you can't play the game at all. You also don't have any way to practice to get better unless you can somehow find players of similar skill level.

author: {'steamid': '76561198102263220', 'num_games_owned': 570, 'num_reviews': 63, 'playtime_forever': 460, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 216, 'last_played': 1502218405}
review:
You want to play a game.
You try to practise.
You have played one hour.
You get kicked.
You try to reach another server.
You get kicked there, too.
You play for 5 mins.
You see a wallshot pro who owns just everything.
You leave the server.
You want to practise more.
You pick a server.
You see that it was the same server where you already got kicked twice.
You get kicked again.
You see no servers with Ping <50ms where you didn´t already got kicked from.
You join a random server.
You suck because you didn´t even complete the tutorial.
You get kicked anyway.
You join a server.
Your IP has been blocked from that server.
You join a cool server.
Game lasts 3min until the next wallshooter pro arrives.
You get kicked because you made your first goal.

Best "Get kicked"-Simulator out there. Buy it! Feel the pain! Get kicked!

11/10

author: {'steamid': '76561198193179266', 'num_games_owned': 272, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 80231, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 3976, 'last_played': 1516823856}
review:
Table of Contents:
- Foreword
- Graphics
- Gameplay
- Sounds
- Controls
- Quality
- Overall Experience


-Foreword
Im not really a Fan of Football games. I dont like Fifa or any other kind of "real" football game.
I played Rocket League which is a pretty good game, but Supraball tops it imo.
I've only spent ~50 Hours playing it so far, im still being pretty bad at the game.

-Graphics
Well, graphics dont really matter that much in Supraball, its amazing though. I like the design of the Characters, the Menu, they put so much effort into detail on different maps, its just amazing.
As i just said, the game is not really about graphics though.

-Gameplay
I really like the gameplay so far, its not really getting boring or anything.
The only thing i hate so far are beginners not passing the ball.
There is a Training Course (which everyone should play), Online Practice, Regular Matches and Ranked Matches. You require 2500 XP to play ranked which you usally get in 1-3 days, depending on how much you play. XP dont get you anything besides the possibility to play ranked so far, but the game is still in Early Access, so i really think it will be more rewarding in the future.
There is not much to say about the gameplay really, its just amazing, you should definetly check it out by yourself!

-Sounds
The Sounds in Supraball are just amazing in every way.
I especially like the sound the figures make when shooting a goal ^^

-Controls
About the Controls, they are easy to learn, but hard to master.
Its pretty easy for beginners, everything is getting explained to you in the Tutorial.
The Tutorial isnt a boring one with some deep Voice talking to you, its just a Practice Course with different Objectives, reaching from Easy to Hard. Even though the game tells you it may take 7 days to learn all of the mechanics, its pretty much done in a few hours. I spent ~3 Hours to complete the course.
You can leave anytime and continue where you quit though.

-Quality
I didnt find any bugs so far, the game looks insanely good though. The Animations are great, just as the graphics and the sounds are. Definetly high quality.

-Overall Experience
My Overall experience was pretty good. I didnt expect the game to be that good.
I got it for free, so my expectations were low, but that game... Its just insanely good.
I'm a huge fan of competitive games, so that may be the reason for me loving it.
I seriously recommend this game to anyone, from any age.
If Steam would finally start to accept star-based ratings, the game would definetly get 5/5.

author: {'steamid': '76561198000167042', 'num_games_owned': 563, 'num_reviews': 29, 'playtime_forever': 2262, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2231, 'last_played': 1506984623}
review:
Pour commencer je dois dire que ce jeu est vraiment addictif.
Dès qu'on commence à y jouer on ne veut plus s'arrêter.

C'est un mélange entre un fps et rocket league mais sans voiture :P


Points positifs:

-Le jeu a de bons graphismes.
-Le gameplay est vraiment amusant et c'est tout de même assez technique.

author: {'steamid': '76561198077774608', 'num_games_owned': 262, 'num_reviews': 24, 'playtime_forever': 255, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 145, 'last_played': 1507683510}
review:
[h1]This an early access review[/h1]

In my opinion the concept of the game is pretty awesome.It's a football game that sets you in first-person perspective.
Maybe you think that is like any other football game but it isn't.It's and unique experience.
Basically you have a gun that can take the ball and throw it to another player from your team and you can also push your enemys with it(sometimes this causes a fault).
Another thing is that you have boost in your legs.This helps you to jump and get the ball.
If and ONLY if(I say that because sometimes devs stop developing their games or make it worse)they continue to develop this game in the good way it will become a must have in the gaming community.
And i hope so cause there aren't enought players and it's hard to find some matches.

author: {'steamid': '76561198228634156', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 1292, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1286, 'last_played': 1585258725}
review:
EDIT: Das Spiel ist mittlerweile kostenlos, weshalb ich jedem empfehlen kann es einfach mal zu probieren. Außerdem sind die Lobbys etwas voller geworden und das Lobbysystem wird auch etwas überarbeitet.

Normal schreibe ich keine reviews und erst recht nicht so früh, aber dieses spiel ist meiner meinung nach eines der besten seit langem. 10€ sind etwas viel, aber im Angebot sollte man sich es am Besten kaufen. Es bietet einen unfassbar guten Multiplayer, den man super mit Freunden spielen kann. Ein Nachteil ist allerdings die nicht wirklich vorhandene Community. Die meisten Lobbys sind leer. Außerdem ist das System etwas schwierig zu verstehen.

+ super Multiplayer
+ Spaß mit Freunden garantiert
+ einfache Steuerung
+ potenzial für anspruchsvolle Spielweisen
+ super Grafik (bis zu 4k)
+ Einsteiger freundlich (gute optionale Tutorials)
+ es gibt guten Support (Updates)
+ viele verschiedene Maps

- relativ leere Lobbys
- komplexes Lobby-system
- etwas teuer

Insgesamt würde ich das Spiel empfehlen. Mein Tipp für Unentschlossene, probiert die zu erst die kostenlose alpha Version aus dem Internet aus. Sie bietet das gesamte Gameplay und ihr könnt sogar im Internet oder im LAN mit Freunden spielen.

author: {'steamid': '76561198077438488', 'num_games_owned': 584, 'num_reviews': 43, 'playtime_forever': 613, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 569, 'last_played': 1469583658}
review:
Considering there aren't many actual reviews for the game yet and it's averaging around 70 players, I thought I'd add my review to maybe persuade you into buying Supraball. Before I start the review, please know that I am one of the players that have played the game since the beta with the old launcher, so I have a few more hours than steam says I've logged.

What is it? 
As you can tell, Supraball is an eSport game that is soccer with guns. You have 4 jumps which you can use to get around, and have a gun that can shoot your ball, pass it to other teammates, or shield the ball. There are 4 positions to be played, Goalkeeper, Defender (Center Back), Midfielder, and Offense (Striker). 

Why should I buy and play it?
Supraball is a game that is easy to pick up and play! The skill floor isn't high at all, and I've been in servers with many newer players just having fun! If you're looking for a casual game to play with your friends, pick it up and join a practice server and play away! Supraball is also a game with a high skill cap. If you're looking for harder competitive play, there are ranked matches with people that really know the mechanics and how to play the game. Whether you're a more casual or hardcore gamer, this game is for you either way!

Not many people are playing it right now - Will I find a match?
Yes! I've been on Supraball with as low as only 20 players and with the server browser and matchmaking, I've still been able to join matches as a substitute and found practice matches that were going on.  The community is a friendly one that is most likely willing to teach you and help you learn from any mistakes you make, so don't be afraid to go in there and, have fun, and try your best!

--Supraball Review--

review:
Most addicting, skillful game i have played since Counter-Strike 1.6.
The gameplay is super fast and skillful as hell, dont expect to buy this game and immediately own people.

But the small community is really nice and instantly got me hooked to keep playing. Even the "Pros" and Devs have no problem playing with newbs and giving tips to improve. Yes even the Devs play this game on a regular basis and its not a rare occasion that they end up in your game.

Other than many different Early-Access games i did NOT have any performance issues or bugs that hindered my fun in any way.

10 / 10 cause the only Problem right now is the small playerbase but thats not something u can blame the Devs for :)

author: {'steamid': '76561198037305786', 'num_games_owned': 2092, 'num_reviews': 116, 'playtime_forever': 208, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 23, 'playtime_at_review': 63, 'last_played': 1712188863}
review:
Searching for a really competitive, funny and new concept of e-sport game ?
Bored of randomness of Rocket League !?
Need to proof that you have more skill than chasing a ball with a car?
This is your game.

+Great ball physics
+Great team work
+A real new type of game,that i've dreamed playing arena games and now is here.
+Skills required to do tricks like curved ball or pirouettes to confuse opponents and score
+Easy to catch, hard to master

-Customisation
-Leveling and consequential matchmaking are absent.
-Game modes, actually only football. But it's an early access so i'm pretty sure that something is in development.

That's all folks, try it!

author: {'steamid': '76561198012563248', 'num_games_owned': 226, 'num_reviews': 17, 'playtime_forever': 84, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 84, 'last_played': 1467457594}
review:
It looks cool and has nice playability. Shame you play with people that doesn't know to play in team. They just look to the goal and always try to score by themselves like they are playing 1v3 or 1v5. It's really sad. And that kind of attitude throws me off of games like this one, that are really promising but the comunity is just sad.

If you don't really care about the other players, go ahead and try the game. If not, don't buy it, because you'll have to chase the ball like a dog to be able to shoot it or pass - if you're a team player like me - to your team mates.

author: {'steamid': '76561198147881130', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 2202, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 1548, 'last_played': 1535997534}
review:
Круто!
Я разложу все по полочкам

1. Графика:
Она сделана в мультяшном стиле,поэтому в этой игре вы не найдете
супер апупенной графики,но линчн мне нравится (Играю на максималках)
2. Геймплей:
Это аркадный футбол (если говорить коротко),просто скажу,вы человечек,который состоит в синей или красной команде
и вам нужно забить как можно больше мячей в ворота соперника,делать это вы будете с помощью пушки,которая может всасывать и выбрасывать мяч (Очень веселый геймплей),но лично от себя советую покупать эту игру вместе с другом,так как там нужен тимплей
3. Оптимизация:
Отличная,не одного проседа FPS за всю игру! (Intel Core i3 2120,GTX 750 Ti,8GB)
Существует всего 2 минуса у этой игры:
1. Цена - я покупал по скидке и скажу так,она не стоит 200 рублей,она стоит 100,может 150,но не больше.
2. Онлайн - он в этой игре маленький,поэтому приготовьтесь к долгому поиску игры.
Итог:
Отличный аркадный футбол,игра затягивает и не смотря на все минусы,она хороша (игра)
8.5/10

author: {'steamid': '76561197996457177', 'num_games_owned': 620, 'num_reviews': 11, 'playtime_forever': 187, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 124, 'last_played': 1511921026}
review:
This game has a lot of promise.  It's very fast paced, very intense, and very easy to pick up and put down.  Game servers can set the match length, so if it runs a little long for you find a smaller time server.  The game is super fast paced, and kickoffs happen just right after another to keep the action and intensity going.  It's a nifty game that would be difficult to master, there's a lot you can do, and team work is key.  It reminds me a lot of Bombing Run from UT2K4 in the way the gun play is handled.  When you have the ball you can charge a shot to make it go farther, and you get points for shooting it in the net, can't run it in like in Bombing Run.

However this game has a key difference in which you can apply all sorts of spin to the ball, and knock other players out.  The spin is applied by hitting Q or E while charing a shot, this gives it air rotation.  If while charing a shot you tap RMB and then Q or E you'll apply spin on the ball when it lands on the ground.  This is useful for getting the ball to your teammates and past goalies.  Combine all that with the fact that you can quad jump and you have a crazy fast-paced indoor soccer arena.

The announcer gets super hyped, and games are easy to get in and out of.

The second thing to note is the community is not fun to play with sometimes.  However on the same note it's a team based game.  You should try to play with people you know and trust rather than randoms online who may scored on their own goal repeatedly or continuously say nasty things to you.  There's a report button if you need it!

Supraball's developers recently changed the XP distribution lately and now defenders and keepers get more points than attackers - of course only if you actually save stuff. A save can get you 25 points, a goal only 20.  So each position is highly valued in the eye of progression and rank.  You don't need to be a striker to stay competitive, goalies are loved as well.

review:
handball on steroids = Supraball

instead of russians u get italians :)
---------------------------------------------------------------------

fun game, but needs improvements to be more awesome and more succesful,especially the esport aspect of the game.it has huge potential to be the next esport game

my suggestions

-remove headbob
-remove splash/dirt effects on screen
-option to disable DoF in the settings

-Should be more quake-like controls/ gravity while jumping.This halo type jumping is a bad choice.

-add statistics to the game,(number of goals,cathes/saves by goal keeper,passes etc..) ingame to be displayed (for spectator mode as well)

-planned feature:"Real matchmaking including queuing with 1 or 2 of your friends"
do not add this to the game, this only cause frustrations and unbalance.Atleast not for ranked.
playing a match with 9 random guy is fun, playing 5v5/3v3 premade is fun too.
playing with 2-3 premades in 5v5/3v3 is very frustrating and allways breaks the game
dont do the same mistake what other developers did, dont make the game frustrating to play pls.


-wallbouncing behind the goal keeper: this is totally unfair and makes the game way too stupid

http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=714770085

between the 2 yellow lines on the picture, the ball should be out, and the goal keeper should get a free kick.
this change will make the game more skillful and more balanced

review:
Играл в эту игру ещё тогда,когда она была в закрытом бета-тесте.
Интересная задумка,видно,что разработчики стараются. Очень интересно узнать,какие в будущем будут обновления у этой игры,надеюсь,что у разработчиков всё получится.
На данный момент очень мало игроков онлайн,в связи с этим была многотысячная раздача игры(а может быть и по иной причине). 
В общем,ждём дальнейших обновлений.

author: {'steamid': '76561198018061433', 'num_games_owned': 1510, 'num_reviews': 1588, 'playtime_forever': 458, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'last_played': 1485615102}
review:
- kostenlos bekommen (über Gleam) -


Besser als gedacht !


+ Läuft ohne Bugs
+ gutes Serversystem
+ Gameplay
+ Profil editieren
+ Erfahrungen sammeln/Rang
+ Grafik
+ Sound
+ Steuerung


Gerade jetzt im Sale für online Multiplayer Spieler wunderbar.
Das tolle Serversystem mit Infos wie viele Spieler auf einem Server sind, welche Positionen noch frei sind usw gefällt mir gut. Man kann verschiedene Positionen besetzen wie als Torwart, Verteidiger oder in der Offensive arangieren. Zwar ist das Gameplay sofort klar und simple, aber es macht einfach Spaß, weil jeder ja anders spielt. Es ist eine andere Art Fußball, denn hier spielt man nicht mit dem Fuß, sondern hat eine Waffe die den Ball auffangen oder wegschießen kann. 


Habe bisher immer Spieler gefunden.

It does not matter if you are a fun of soccer/football/whatever game with balls, you will probably enjoy it, especially if played with friends.

What the game needs at time of writing:

Better GUI.
More comprehensible training/tutorial.
Different game modes (eg: more arcade, more strict rules, more player with huge maps, less player with small maps, etc... those are just some ideas)

author: {'steamid': '76561198095902787', 'num_games_owned': 257, 'num_reviews': 33, 'playtime_forever': 646, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 236, 'last_played': 1492818274}
review:
okay, so after playing with a cool fellow named "your mom" and actually learning some of the basics, and some tips and tricks, i see how the game can be really good, it has potential.

Unfortunatly, the tutorial COULD use some help, maybe a step by step tutorial teaching you the basics would be better than throwing you in a hallway with signs that are half the size of an ant.



OLD REVIEW --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

"The most toxic community I have ever played with. Noobs get no help and are pub stomped by 
insane skill level players. There is no one playing the game at any given moment." - DittyKong
I entrily Agree with this, when i joined the first time i thought oh, this looks like a very low pop server, but then i realised that was about the ONLY server, the game itself has a good idea, just this game doesn't portay it correxctly, if they added something like this to rocket leauge i'd be intrested. But other than that the tutorial sucks, no step by step help, its either get into online match or practice and figure out 3 things. Don't get me started on the launcher "design" As a new player, i had no idea what the 250 buttons did, please fix this game, maybe it could be revived.

author: {'steamid': '76561198110455465', 'num_games_owned': 387, 'num_reviews': 14, 'playtime_forever': 2095, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 157, 'last_played': 1533268971}
review:
Everything about this game is new and exciting, this is newest inventive sport game that has grabbed my attention next to Rocket League. It takes time to learn and master the game, and having little to no player base right now leaves very few chances to actually grasp the concept and understand it, but all it takes is one steam sale to grow the player base and make this game super fun again. Although i have only played two hours on steam, I played it back before it was on greenlight with friends, and it felt so good to finally pay for it on relive it.

The community is simply just old Deathball (original game before supraball) players that have been playing since the games conception and instabought it when it became available on steam. Asking them for help in game is your best shot at learning to be honest, and most of them will be willing to help you. They love this game and want it to be as great and busy as it used to be, so crushing noobs that don't know any better won't help when they are on your team later.

The community is small right now, but will fill up. The developers know this issue and really want it to fill up. They are very transperant in all of their announcements and have all players (especially new ones) in mind. They have recently updated a bunch of tutorials for the true beginners, and then the community is always nice in game and will help you.

This is a great game, well worth the $20 once the community fills up and sales start happening. It pains me to see such bad reviews because few people have bought it yet. It is a good game, its unfortunate the player base is still small but will surely pick up. It is fun when there are people to play with, and I have yet to run into anyone that is rude or mean. Just alot of old wise Supraball players that have been playing before it was even named Supraball.

Basically, Yes the community is small and hard to find matches, but this is the beginning of something bigger. When the community picks up so will this game, but i still highly recommend it.

author: {'steamid': '76561198174742861', 'num_games_owned': 164, 'num_reviews': 8, 'playtime_forever': 514, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 244, 'last_played': 1496757785}
review:
Общее впечатление об игре:
Игра заинтересовала меня с самого просмотра трейлера. Но не все так просто как показалось. Игра очень динамична, и без хорошей наследственной (из других игр) реакции Вам там делать нечего.
Плюсы:
+ Простое и удобное управление.
+ Качественная картинка.
+ Интересная задумка.
+ Проект продолжает развиваться.
+ Хорошо продуманные правила игры.

Минусы:
- Самый первый минус и пожалуй главный- это оптимизация. Она просто ужасна. Мой комп с неплохим 4-х ядерным i5 процессором и видеокартой Nvidia GeForce 940 на 2 гб просто рыдали и кричали. Они умоляли меня выйти из игры. Стандартные видеонастройки выдавали 10-15 кадров в секунду. И что вы думаете? Я уменьшил все по минимуму. Показатель увеличился до 30-35 кадров, но этого по прежнему мало. Пришлось воспользоваться нестандартными методами, а именно настройка графики через панель управления видеокартой. После тщательной настрйки, я увеличил показатель до 100-120 кадров в секунду. Картинка же почти не изменилась.
- Второй минус и он же менее важный - это то, что могут попадаться достаточно опытный противники, которые не удостоят Вас, даже пасса с их стороны. Мне встречались игроки, которы готовы были Богу душу отдать, а не пасс жалкому новичку. Дабы не быть жалким, пришлось потратить пару часов, на выучивание необходимых движений и финтов.

На этом я пожалуй закончу. Всем удачной игры. Если кому-то нужна помощь по настройке видеокарты, пишите в личку.

author: {'steamid': '76561198000127751', 'num_games_owned': 708, 'num_reviews': 34, 'playtime_forever': 7536, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4392, 'last_played': 1540756667}
review:
[b] Stand 22.06.2016 [/b]

2 größere Updates sind eingespielt worden. 
Diese haben zum einen den Launcher verändert und was wesentlich wichtiger ist, ein Tutorial eingefügt. Dieses funktioniert bis auf kleinere Schöhnheitsfehler sehr gut.

[b] Stand Review vom 14.05.2016	[/b]

Sollte man sich Supraball zulegen?

Wenn man Supraball einmal näher betrachtet, dann stellt man fest, dass es eine wunderschöne Grafik hat. Das zeigt sich insbesondere in der Gestaltung der verschiedenen Maps. Dabei spielt es keine Rolle, ob man sich auf den 3 vs 3 oder 5 vs 5 Karten wiederfindet. Auf einigen Spielfeldern erzeugt die dargestellte Kulisse schon ein Gefühl davon, als würde man sich in einem echten Sportstadion befinden. 
Allem in allem ist aber wohl die UE3 Engine für die schöne Optik maßgebend.

Das Spiel ist noch nicht komplett, aber man kann sofort loslegen und spielen. Das bedeutet, es werden viele Server gestellt, die genutzt werden können, um normale Partien zu spielen. Fakt ist, dass es [b] spielbereit [/b] ist! 
Der Schlüssel zum Sieg ist oftmals Taktik und Teamwork.

Supraball erhält mehrmals kleinere Updates pro Monat und es wird auch stetig an größeren Veränderungen gearbeitet.



[u] Kritik: [/u]


Supraball befindet sich zurecht im Status des EA. Viele Dinge fehlen noch und müssen hinzugefügt werden.

Das Hauptproblem sind die geringen Spielerzahlen. Hier sollte in naher Zukunft das Hauptaugenmerk in der Werbung neuer Spieler liegen. Wie jedes gute Multiplayerspiel macht Supraball umso mehr Spaß je mehr Spieler es sich kaufen und auch spielen. 

Als Anfänger in Supraball hat man es leider noch recht schwer. Die Bedienbarkeit vom Hauptmenü ist zwar sehr übersichtlich, allerdings wird man Ingame sehr alleine gelassen. 
Es sollte dringend an der Erstellung eines Tutorials gearbeitet werden. Da bloßes "abgucken" nicht genug sein kann.
ABER: Hilfreich ist vorallem die aktuell bestehende Community, die Fragen beantwortet.

Was vorallem fehlt sind Features zur Individualisierung des eigenen Charackters. Mittlerweile ist es möglich ein eigenes Team zu erstellen, welchem andere Spieler auch beitreten können.
Weitere Features sind angekündigt und werden in naher Zukunft auch eingefügt werden



[b] Mein Fazit:	[/b]

Auch wenn Supraball sehr unfertig in äußeren Bereichen und wenig einsteigerfreundlich ist, sollte man den Schritt trotzdem wagen und es sich zulegen. Am besten mit ein paar Leuten mit denen man es erstmal unter sich spielen kann. So findet man am besten ins Spiel hinein und wird auch auf lange Sicht viel Freude damit haben.

Ich persönlich hatte viel Spaß und hab es auch immernoch!

review:
Rocked League in Egoperspektive und mit echtem Ballgefühl (wenn man die Steuerung beherrscht).

Für Shooter Fans einen Versuch wert. Immernoch zu wenige Spieler von denen viele sehr erfahren sind(von früheren Versionen), deshalb ist man als Anfänger sehr im nachteil.
Leider zu komplexe Steuerung mit der nicht jeder klar kommt.

Ein "Basic Modus" mit den einfachsten Steuerelementen würde Abhilfe schaffen da einige die Steuerung so gut beherrschen das sie den Ball ansaugend, das Schild an habend, fliegend im Kreis drehen um den Ball dann schlussendlich mit einem Schild Shock ins Triangel befördern.
Sorry aber sowas können selbst mit Übung nur die wenigsten leute.


Das Spielprenzip ist wirklich gut und wird in Zukunft vielleicht noch erfolgreich.

author: {'steamid': '76561198058479270', 'num_games_owned': 92, 'num_reviews': 5, 'playtime_forever': 153543, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 38614, 'last_played': 1673815150}
review:
Jedna z lepszych gier w które grałem. Ta gra jak żadna inna stawia na zgranie ze swoją drużyną i teamwork, które są podstawą do wygranej. Proste zasady - zdobywać bramki. Proste sterowanie za pomocą WSADu + Myszki, które każdy ogarnie po paru minutach aby w miare podawać i strzelać, jednak aby kręcić niesamowite triki i zdobywać szalone bramki wymaga wiele czasu i treningów. W grze zaimplementowany został system rang, osobny dla ciebie i dla twojej drużyny, oraz twoje statystyki gdzie pokazany jest każdy aspekt twojej gry.
Ta gra dobitnie pokaże ci co to znaczy mieć dobry refleks i aim. Gdy będziesz ze zdumieniem patrzył jak ktoś broni podkręconą piłke mknącą z prędkości kilkaset km/h pokonującą pół boiska w ułamek sekundy. W tej grze nie chodzi o to aby śledzić gdzie jest teraz piłka. W tej grze chodzi o to aby przewidywać gdzie piłka będzie za chwile. W supraballu nie ma czegoś takiego jak RNG. Każda akcja, każde podanie, każdy strzał zależy tylko od ciebie i twoich umiejętności.
