author: {'steamid': '76561198004532205', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 6, 'playtime_forever': 24614, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 10172, 'last_played': 1590883254}
review:
Wall of text! \o/

One of the few games I happily spent some money on. However I don't really recommend doing the same thing for new players. But let me explain.



I have no clue when did I get hooked into the game. Probably I saw someone streaming the game and decided to try it out. It was free to download, it was in alpha and it was quite fun. A few skilled players taught me the most important moves and tricks and I slowly figured out how these things work. And then I got a Closed beta key for free and after that, we're here.

I knew what awaited me when I bought the game. No risk for me (aside from the usual "it's a dead game *hurr durr* waste of money"). I enjoy it because I know what I am, and other players are capable of. As a new player it's risky because you'll either like it or not. A free weekend or a lowered price definitely needed for "the casual" players to try this out.

And yes, the price. It's quite high for a game that "lacks content". True! But the developers will add more and more and it will be more diverse, especially if we'll have a bigger community to play with. I bet they're not going to stop right here, when they're halfway through the marathon.

The development also seem a bit slow. Maybe they'll release everything at once, and that's why it takes so long? I don't know. However I'm not a programmer, I don't know how hard it is to create a game and new contents so I'm not judging.

The early access misses some really needed content, like tutorials. Of course, there's an online "How to play" article which can be found on the official website but who reads that. It would be a really good idea to read it, though... :D You might not know what those things are but after you try those in-game, I'm sure you will figure it out. If not, and you need some advice, most of the skilled players are there to help. We currently have a small playerbase and we surely don't want to lose it because of some confusing game elements.



But the core of the game has been layed down for a while now. It's lovely, it's simple and yet so fun if you get a hang of it. Of course you are going to get a bit frustrated if you get knocked out like 10 times in a match because you weren't fast enough with the ball, but as you progress these frustrations will be gone and you start enjoying the game (like I did). You start feeling that you can do better, whatever happened can be done in a different (and better) way even if it was your fault. You'll watch out for it next time. And who knows, maybe you'll score that winning goal or you save a last second shot in a tight match. ^_^

Even though there's a few cons about this game and can be considered risky, I definitely recommend this game if you like what you see.

EDIT: Fixed some grammar mistakes ( I hope xD ). Thanks for the heads up. o/

author: {'steamid': '76561198012883252', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 37, 'playtime_forever': 203, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 62, 'last_played': 1465582126}
review:
It's literally football/soccer, but without the dribbling. I've only played an hour so far, but I can tell you I love it. 

It has the same feel and speed of the real thing.  You can do things like put topspin or slice on the ball, alter the power of your shots, and pass it to other players with ease. It's a little lacking in terms of UI and polish, and there's not a real tutorial to speak of, but the game feels great and is satisfying to play.

review:
EDIT: One of the developers added me on Steam to get some input from me and he was actually quite a nice guy. He took on board my thoughts, put in a bug request from an issue I had and really professional the whole time. I will probably try the game again on a free weekend in the future.

I'm not really sure how this game has been in development since 2012. The launcher is horrible, the graphics could be beaten by a flash game and it is all basically an eyesore.

I know a lot of people really seem to like the game but I just can't understand the hype. The game was boring, felt clunky and didn't feel worth the £11 or so I paid for it.

I know somebody is going to say "Oh, but it's in Early Access!!1!".. It's been in development for 4 years, critism is completely valid.

review:
Hier ein kleiner Ausschnitt aus meinen Erfahrungen:

Mein Review:
Endlich mal wieder ein Game, was mich voll packt. Meiner Meinung nach genauso viel Potential wie Rocket League. Mir gefällt es sogar noch ne Nummer mehr, weil:

1) Mehr Bewegungsfreiheit
2) Ego-Perspektive (gibt einem echt das Gefühl auf nem Bolzplatz oder am Strand zu sein (je nach Setting)

4) Geilere Spielzüge möglich

Im TS wird das einfach Mega sein. Als Zuschauer ist es glaub ich auch wesentlich spannender als Rocket League (Aber das ist nur meine Meinung)

Des Weiteren habe ich gehört & gelesen, dass es mit der Zeit ein Upgrade auf Unreal Engine 4 geben wird. Ich bin echt gespannt. Das war genau das was ich mal wieder gebraucht habe...

review:
A game easy to play, but hard to master.

I never really got into the Beta, as it felt more laggy than the alpha-experience. I still have unusual bad ping in this version of the game, but I think that doesn't worry me much.

Supraball has a lot of potential, a dev-team and community with many ideas. 

A cool game to play with friends together and even cooler to play competetiv in a team against other teams. 

I think the price which it is atm is too high for the stand of the current game. 

But I've seen the devs hard work over these years and truly belive, that they are going to use that money in the best interest.

author: {'steamid': '76561198299094813', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 3372, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 2208, 'last_played': 1482787555}
review:
Aesthetically weak and uninspired, unoptimized, stagnant, feature-starved. These are just a few descriptors that I feel accurately represent the state of Supraball. 

When buying a new game, I am often curious as to what creative energy went into bringing it to fruition. Supraball is a downgrade from the original mod in terms of art direction. This being the case primarily because Deathball used UT2K4 assets. Deathball had hundreds of user-created maps, a plethora of player models, replays, pausing, and in-game ready system, a more sophisticated kickoff system, better in-game stat tracking, and more gameplay variety. A UT2K4 mod, that had been in development for two years, had far more going on for it feature-wise than a standalone game that has, according to the dev team, been “in the works” for four years. Being a programmer, I understand the challenges behind creating something like this. However, the dev team chose to price the game at $20. Rocket League also costs $20. Rocket League is far ahead of Supraball in almost every area one could think of, and the dev team has invited this comparison via their pricing decision. 

Gameplay-wise, Supraball is nearly the perfect type of game for me. That I cannot recommend it to most gamers should be a red flag. If you put in the time, a high-level game of Supraball can be more interesting and enjoyable than perhaps any other game I’ve played. It’s that you have to look past the poor art direction, underdeveloped visuals, missing features, nonsensical rank and lobby system, and the very steep learning curve (assuming you want to play in the higher-level games, which is where Supraball becomes far more interesting). In the hands of the right dev team, this type of game could be very successful, as you’ve seen with something like Rocket League. The Rocket League dev team listens to their community, has been a lot of creative energy into their game, and seems to generally “get it”. I cannot say the same for Supraball’s dev team. If you’re looking for something similar to Rocket League in concept, that gives you more control over what’s going on, and has, in my opinion, superior overall gameplay, buy Supraball. Just know that there are several glaring things that you must overlook, and I don’t feel that the vast majority of players are willing to or should have to. If you’re buying this game based on an expectation that it will continue to evolve, don’t. If the game were priced under $10 USD, I feel it would be easier for me to recommend. At $20… No.
developer_response: The comment about us having taken code from Deathball and porting it to Supraball is wrong. Every single line was rewritten. We are not open source, so this statement is completely made up.

author: {'steamid': '76561198053962548', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 15244, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 4980, 'last_played': 1593116738}
review:
Questo gioco è fenomenale. All'inizio pensavo fosse il classico giochino da quattro soldi, invece si è rivelato, nel suo piccolo, un capolavoro. Il gameplay è ben fatto, la fisica idem anche se raramente succedono cose "strane". Apprezzo in particolare le mappe, per nulla banali e anche i suoni li ritengo ben fatti (anche se raramente si buggano). L'unica pecca a mio avviso è il matchmaking, inoltre ho riscontrato un problema ovvero quando si entra in una partita già iniziata la hud sparisce e vedi solamente il tuo personaggio, quindi niente score, niente nomi, niente chat ecc. fortunatamente basta rimanere per un'altra partita e il problema sparisce. In definitiva consiglio questo gioco ma attenzione! Può sembrare facile ma giocare bene è veramente difficile.
AGGIORNAMENTO
Forse la community è una delle peggiori che abbia mai provato, gente che vi kicka a caso perché vogliono essere padroni del server roba mai vista, inoltre già non sono presenti molti giocatori se poi vi kickano a caso dall'unico server con giocatori beh potete tranquillamente chiudere il gioco e passare ad altro. Per questo motivo sconsiglio l'acquisto, purtroppo pure qui i bambini del cazzo rovinano tutto.
Aggiornamento 2: la situazione sembra migliorata grazie anche ai saldi di steam che ha portato molta gente nuova.

author: {'steamid': '76561198120562345', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 702, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 384, 'last_played': 1504491001}
review: I am new to the game, and only 4 hours in as of this review. I get absolutely spanked most games, but I don't rage quit. Instead I strive to be better, so that I can be the spanker someday. Obviously there are veterans on here that have played much longer than most people, so expect to get tag teamed by gorillas every now and then until you hone your skills in a practice server. Don't be salty about losing, because you will adapt overtime and become a more adept player. You have to work as a team, and you have to have fast reflexes. The movement is like that of Unreal Tournament, so 12 year olds be damned. You can strafe dash left and right, and you can quad jump in the air, which is incredibly useful in avoiding a nice kick to the face. You can put a backspin, front spin, or a side spin on the ball, which confuses even the most hardened gods sometimes. Passing is easy too, but it's also very easy to intercept as well, so git gud. All in all, it's a great game with some relation to Rocket League, but don't call it a Rocket League rip off, because this came out before it. See you on the field fam.

author: {'steamid': '76561198026789044', 'num_games_owned': 286, 'num_reviews': 127, 'playtime_forever': 228, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 228, 'last_played': 1488337166}
review:
Хотя эту игру я уже видел в 2014 году, но не смог обойти вниманием её и в 2016. Из плюсов - необычный геймплей. Это одна из первых кибер-спортивных игр, где можно играть от первого лица. Ощущение, что ты играешь в шутер. Во-вторых - управление. Здесь тебе и выбор сила выстрела с подкрутками, и возможность отнять мяч у соперника. Туча скрытых возможностей по типу ведение мяча и применение необычного вида подкрутки. Разумеется, не всё сразу получается хорошо, но если тренироваться - непременно станешь матёрым супраболистом. Мой четырёхминутрый ролик о моих ощущениях после первых 30 мин игры:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DYHcQYK5zzU

PS: Тем, кому немного не хватает денег на покупку игры - я постараюсь помочь. Пишите в личку.

author: {'steamid': '76561197963814795', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 81156, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 40081, 'last_played': 1691438154}
review:
I have been playing this game for 2 years since it has been in development, and I still look forward to spending hours playing after I get home from work. I have made some awesome friends, and some great memories. I have played in tournaments, ranked matches, and just messed around on a public server. All 3 totally different experiences with this game, and all equally enjoyable. Some matches end with my palms sweaty, my heart pacing, and my armpits soaked. Nothing I have ever played before has matched this intensity. This game can be really fast if you have the right group of experienced players. If you love sports, and are competitive in nature, this game is for you. 

You have the ability to create teams, particiapte in tournaments, build up your rank and stats, and become a legendary goalie, defender, or midfielder that others will look up to. There's just so much to say about this game, that I can't even begin to explain it.  If you're interested in the least bit, take a chance on this game, I highly doubt that you will regret it.

I hope to see you on the pitch!

author: {'steamid': '76561198015799541', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 4, 'playtime_forever': 17728, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 12438, 'last_played': 1517527386}
review:
-##-
Disclaimer:
I started playing Supraball 2013 and was part of the closed testing enviroment.
-##-

Supraball is a First-Person-Soccer game. It rewards fast paced teamoriented plays. It reminds me a little of Valves majorly underappriciated game Ricochet where movement and precision are key to a high level play. This can be frustrating for new players as the introduction and succes are depending on utilisation of creative and advance mechanics. 
The visuals are simple yet pleasing and that results in a low hardware demand. A PC as strong as a PS4 should run it on medium settings.

Pros:
-Simple yet pleasing visuals
-Solid game mechanics
-Teamwork decides victory
-Rewarding and broad learning curve
-addictive for fooball/soccer lovers
-Not demanding towards Hardware

Cons:
-Not intuitive configuration of controls (new players should configure during practice alone [May.2016] as the launcher is still buggy)
-Sound Options are lacking
-Minor bugs in the launcher
-Launcher still needs a major overhaul
-Price and content not matching

author: {'steamid': '76561198050278597', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 175855, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 122868, 'last_played': 1699105250}
review:
The only negative thing I have to say about Supraball is the fact that it's SO GOOD that it has made almost every other game seem boring and mundane to me. I've played this game since August of 2014 and have never experienced a dull moment. If you are into competitive games then Supraball is a must. The amount of teamwork and the infinite amount of strategies you can come up with has made this game an all time favorite for me. It's a great game for both casual and competitive players with some of the most complex and unique game mechanics in any game i've ever played. Playing this game is like entering a time machine. 5 hours feel like 30 minutes and each game plays out differently from the next. Supraball also has a very high skill cap and incredible e-sport potential. I'm telling you guys, this game is a gem and there is no other game like it.

10/10 would recommend

* Its been 2 years and all I can say is CALL FOR HELP SOS. Its a wasteland out here folks. The only people who play are about 15 of the same alpha players who cant stop playing cause most of us are addicted af and its a shitshow. If you are going to play the game, you're going to need to bring 9 of your friends, or even better, 1000 of your friends because you wont find real games otherwise.

5/10 would recommend if you are a maniac like us

author: {'steamid': '76561198025091623', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 65549, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 55894, 'last_played': 1590353257}
review:
All the time I spent playing this game it was always fun but never the same. 
In the beginning it's messing around on the pitch, learning controls, scoring your first goals, catch some balls as a keeper.
Then it's like learning volleys and improving precision, then getting better reflexes in goal.
Then a deep dive into teamplay and tactics, forming a team with friends and playing matches against other teams.
Then it's becoming creative and using the means you have to create ever new plays, juke defenders and keepers.
Then it's participating in a community league and getting to the top of the ladder.
Then it's winning a close yet so important game by your hands last second.
Lastly it's being carried away in ecstasy.

No regrets, perfect 5/7!

author: {'steamid': '76561198012195560', 'num_games_owned': 166, 'num_reviews': 2, 'playtime_forever': 11366, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 7396, 'last_played': 1661673527}
review:
Je fais rarement des review sur steam mais la  après +120h de jeu passer sur l'alpha puis la bêta je pense que mon avis peut vous intéressez. 

Donc Supraball un fps-foot reprennent le principe d'un mod d'Unreal Tournament 2003 et 2004. Le but étant de marquer des buts comme dans un vrai match de foot, mais cette fois-ci  sans les pieds, mais plutôt avec un gun qui vous servira à récupérer la balle faire des passe etc ... vous prendrez place dans des match d'une durée de 10 à 20 minutes en 3v3 ou 5v5 sur différente map neige, soleil avec un toit sans toit bref tout un tas de map.

Les graphismes sont très simplistes ce qui rend le jeu assez accessible pour toutes les config et est parfaitement adapté a ce genre de jeu dit e-sportif ou la clarté et très importante pour pouvoirs commenter un match facilement.

Le gameplay est difficile à prendre en main au début il vous faudra un peu de temps pour vous y habituer et commencer à faire des "tricks" (dribble ou action permettent de dépasser un adversaire) le niveau de jeux en équipe est plus important que le niveau individuelle même si les gardiens font souvent une différence énorme dans les parties.

Conclusion : un jeu mélangent fun à plusieurs ou complètement try hard grâce au système de ladder/rank des parties rapides demandant du skill où vous pourrez vous améliorer au fil des game. Moi j'achète et vous ?

author: {'steamid': '76561198041995904', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 120094, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 114763, 'last_played': 1581297977}
review:
EDIT: [strike] I just can't recommend the game right now due to the lack of players. When the playercount increases to the point where you can fairly easily get into a game with people at similar skill levels to you I'll remove this edit. Just bear in mind the low playercount if you're considering buying the game. [/strike] 

EDIT 2: Since the game is now free there's really no reason not to try it. As of 10th September 2017 the playercount is such that you can pretty quickly find a game, and if there are empty spots the bots are pretty reasonable to play with.

[b] Innovative, addictive and incredibly satisfying. Whether you have played for 1 hour or 1,000 hours the awesome feeling you get from being a part of epic plays never fades. The game is quite unpolished but if you can see through the clunky UI and lacking features there is a great game beneath. As with a lot of Early Access games, it's a diamond in the rough. [/b]

[h1] Supraball in comparison to Rocket League: [/h1]
[url=https://www.reddit.com/r/RocketLeague/comments/4c20hs/apparently_pc_had_its_own_version_of_sarpbc_on/d1fhe33] [b] "Deathball..." (the predecessor of Supraball) "... was one of the main reasons why Rocket League exists" - Psyonix Adam on Reddit [/b] [/url]
I expect this comparison is what a lot of people will be wanting to know. I'll preface this section by saying I have about 650 ingame hours in Rocket League and about 2,000 in Supraball. [b] Rocket League gave me a very similar feeling of excitement that I got from Supraball when I first started playing. [/b] Deep down at their core they are essentially the same game - put the ball in the goal, just with different methods of doing so. Both are very pure, simple games which give you some basic controls and then set you free to do what you wish. 
[b] I feel like Supraball gives you a lot more ways to be creative [/b] and play the game though to the degree that every second of the game you are holding the ball the tree of your choices branches 100 times: will you do a little rollspin to juke a defender, will you pass to a teammate who is boosted and flying across the map for a volley combo, will you panic and do a horrible pass back to your keeper and score a hilarious own goal or will you do the countless other things available to you? [b] More complex plays are also far more accessible in Supraball, [/b] within 100 hours of play you can be setting up strong charge to volley goals to score 300km/h screamer goals, whereas in Rocket League setting up a pass play like this is far, far more difficult. [b] The autolock pass also makes passing very easy and allows new players to perform teamplay quite easily. [/b] Now let's move onto the pro's and con's of Supraball in it's Early Access State.


[h1] Pros: [/h1]
+++ [b] It's free. [/b] The monetization now comes from a chest/key system. 
+++ [b] Every match plays differently. [/b] There are so many different ways to play that you never end up playing the same game twice.[b] It has the "just 1 more match" feeling and so can be very addictive and has huge replayability. [/b]
+++ [b] 4 unique positions to play: Goalkeeper, Defender, Midfielder and Striker. [/b] You can sink thousands of hours into a position and still have room to learn and innovate. Or, don't conform to the meta, you're free to play however you want!
++ [b] The skill ceiling is disgustingly high [/b], I have sunk probably 2000 hours into goalkeeping in the Alpha/Beta and I'm not even close to the skill cap. The skill floor is pretty high too, but even when you first start playing and have no idea what you're doing it is still really enjoyable
++ Applying curves and combinations of curves to your shots gives huge variety to the gameplay and [b] lots of opportunities for creative, unique and flashy plays [/b]
++ [b] A short in-game tutorial and some follow up tutorial videos really help you to get to grips with the high skill floor. [/b] The game has alot to learn and the tutorial covers all of the basics, with some sections (such as the goalkeeper training) which are even useful to me with a few thousand hours playtime.
++ [b] Bots have been added and they are surprisingly okay to play with. 
+ [b] Intuitive and fairly simple controls [/b] similar to most FPS games
+ [b] There's something for everyone [/b]. Public matches are more casual and relaxed and ranked is more serious. It's enjoyable to play even if you typically don't like sports games like myself.
+ Multiple varients of the 3v3 and 5v5 maps (similar to Rocket League) with different visual styles
+ Even if this game does not do too well and has a small playerbase (eg. 50 to 100 players) it can still be fun. The whole time I have played from 0 to 2000 hours there has probably been an average of 40 players online and even so it is a blast.

[h1] Ehhh: [/h1]
~Only 2 game modes (3v3 and 5v5) though both gamemodes focus on very different ways of playing
~[b] Curved shots bouncing off of walls are unintuitive but add a huge amount of depth to the game [/b] that allows crazy solo wall jukes and is why the striker position is viable

[h1] Cons: [/h1]
--- [b] A clunky UI and missing lots of useful features such as easily partying with friends, good matchmaking and team matchmaking (these features are planned). [/b] The lobby system has matchmaking within it to balance teams but there is no way to easily queue and join a match like you can in Rocket League.
-- [b] For some people the optimisation is god awful even on a monster rig, for others the game runs perfectly on a terrible computer. [/b]
[strike] -- [b] The price is based on the gameplay and potential of future content, not the amount of content it has right now. [/b] This game is priced similarly to Rocket League, but doesn't have any of the extra features. You may want to hold off on purchasing until these features are added if they are important to you. This problem has been mostly solved by the significant (50% ish) price drop. [/strike]
-The devs "rely on the community renting the majority of servers", which is certainly not something I'm used to in my games and seems very strange to me
- Despite what the steam store says [b] the game is fairly unpolished, [/b] lacking a lot of nice little features like cosmetics or unlockables
- Whilst the game can be played by ignoring your teammates, utilising them properly is the best way to play. This might not appeal to some pure solo players
- [b] Some bugs can affect the mid to high level of play, [/b] include random weird bounces off of walls and occasionally your shield not working. These are almost entirely unnoticeable in the first 100 hours of play though and will hopefully be patched

[b] tl;dr: It's basically meth [/b]

Edit: The default controls can be a bit wonky, I would advise changing the following:
"Pass" to RMB, "Kick" to LMB, "Pull-Catch" to left shift, "Quickshot" to Middle Mouse. "Shield" to RMB and the others whatever you feel comfortable with. If you want to goalkeep, turn "double tap dash" off and set the "Dash Jump" key to something you feel comfortable with.

author: {'steamid': '76561197989976642', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 1, 'playtime_forever': 27606, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 25857, 'last_played': 1551831068}
review:
I have always been a fan of team sports, especially those that involve advancing an object to an opposing goal, like football, basketball, and hockey.  There are constant individual moves and coordinated team strategies going on that make each sport beautiful.  Any amazing effort or foolish mistake can mean success or failure.  This is Supraball.

Supraball can be enjoyed on a casual level, but competitive Supraball really shines.  Your teammates are counting on you.  Your heart is pounding; your adrenaline flowing.  I have never experienced this from any other video game.

The game is in early access.  I look forward to more features, and improved polish.  The gameplay is great, but it still needs features like instant replay to be a great full release.

Regardless, I've had years of fun playing Supraball and it's predecessor, Deathball.  It's a great game and it has huge potential.  It gives lazy, fat gamers like me the same feeling I'm sure professional athletes get.

author: {'steamid': '76561198058033779', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 10, 'playtime_forever': 12, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 12, 'last_played': 1447543959}
review:

author: {'steamid': '76561198035312118', 'num_games_owned': 1153, 'num_reviews': 12, 'playtime_forever': 188, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 188, 'last_played': 1462209139}
review:
Supraball est un très bon jeu multijoueur et je me suis beaucoup amusé lors des quelques parties que j'ai pu faire pendant la bêta. 

Comparé à un Rocket League le jeu peut sembler un peu fade mais le gameplay est original et les parties dynamiques surtout si vous jouez entre amis. Par contre encore peu de joueurs présents (l'ouverture en early access en ramenera sans doute ! En tout cas j'espère). Les règles sont plutôt simples même si les contrôles demandent un peu d'entrainement avant d'être bien maitrisés. 

Dernier point, les mises à jour et corrections de bugs ont été réguliers et les développeurs semblent très impliqués et motivés pour améliorer le jeu. De bonne augure pour la suite !

author: {'steamid': '76561198037941066', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 18, 'playtime_forever': 23520, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 23099, 'last_played': 1505327246}
review:
[h1]Mon point de vue en tant que alpha/beta-testeur ( plus d'un ans ) :[/h1]

Supraball est un FPS de Foot Arcade qui se veut compétitif.
Le gameplay est très rapide et le teamplay est la clé du succès.
Tout est basé sur le jeu d'équipe. 
Même les déplacements sont plus efficaces (plus radipes) avec l'aide d'un coéquipier.
Exemple : il est possible de pousser son coéquipier pour qu'il gagne en vitesse et atteigne sa position plus rapidement.

Gameplay a "Haut niveau" - Duke Nukem jouant a Supraball : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HtNn8q7-KZk

Chaque personne sur le terrain est un vrai joueur, finit les IA merdiques !
C'est merveilleux en équipe, mais peut aussi être frustrant lorsque vous jouez avec des inconnus, car chaque joueur est extrêmement important et un seul point faible peut faire perdre son équipe.
Ceci peut engendrer une communauté agressive comme tout les jeux compétitifs...

[u]Points négatifs:[/u]
- Le prix, 20e c'est beaucoup trop chère pour un jeu comme celui la. Entre 5 et 10 euro aurait été plus adéquate.
- A "haut" niveau je trouve que le gameplay bride la créativité des joueurs et tout le monde joue de la même facon.
- Les développeurs, le jeu évolu extrêmement lentement.
- Le système de Matchmaking est lent, incomplet et plus compliqué que les autres jeux [Surement corrigé avant la vrai sortie du jeu].

[u]Points Possitifs:[/u]
- Gameplay aux petits oignons, fluide et rapide.
- Un style de jeu orignial et très rare ( Un FPS de foot avec 0 IA, rien que ca rend le jeu super interessant ).
- Les différentes positions : Gardien de But, Défenseur, Milieu et Attaquant rendent le jeu varié ( chaque positions sont vraiment différentes en terme de gameplay )
- Les Tricks ( il est possible de faire des "figures" ou dribbles plutot sympas ) Exemple le Sucker Trick :https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=owRZUC9uEQQ
- Le jeu est optimisé pour la compétition.
